title: gramma mary's french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.

title: broccoli cheese rice casserole
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and celery in oleo. Cook until tender. Add soup, Cheez Whiz and broccoli; stir. Add rice and mix well. Place mixture in 2-quart casserole dish; top with crushed chips. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shanghai noodles with spicy beef sauce
directions: Heat wok or large skillet until hot; add the oil, garlic, gingerroot and pepper flakes.
Saute about 5 seconds.
Add onion; stir-fry until onion is transparent.
Crumble in ground beef; stir-fry until the meat is light brown.
In a small bowl, combine 1/4 cup chicken broth, hoisin sauce, soy sauce and sherry/broth. Stir into meat mixture.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring once or twice.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water for 6 to 8 hours.
Cook beans 3 plus hours.
Add sausage and bring to a boil.
Add rice and spices. Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: wild and cheesy chicken
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Melt butter in saucepan and add bell pepper, green onions and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cover vegetables with water and boil gently for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add salt and seasonings.
Add tomato juice.
Simmer at least 30 minutes (longer if chopped tomatoes are used).
Serve hot with crackers or cornbread.

title: homemade ice cream(peppermint)
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk, half and half, flavoring and peppermint sticks (crushed).
Fill the ice cream container the rest of the way with milk.
For electric or manual ice cream freezer.

title: gazpacho
directions: Put all the ingredients in a blender, except the bread crumbs and liquify.
Strain mixture and reserve the liquid.
Add enough bread crumbs to slightly thicken the liquid.
Chill and serve garnished with cucumber cubes and ice.
Can also be served unstrained and without the bread cubes.

title: rocky road brownies no. 2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and margarine in microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in sugar until well blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour until well mixed.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle marshmallows, then chocolate chips and nuts over brownies.
Continue baking 3 to 5 minutes until topping begins to melt together.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares. Makes 24 brownies.

title: finadene sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir.
This sauce may be used on rice, meat or chicken.

title: matthew c. chicken
directions: Brown chicken and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soups and water together and add to chicken.
Top with cooked stuffing. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and cook 20 minutes longer.
Top with rice.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease large pie plate.
Layer cottage and Parmesan cheese in plate.
Mix beef, herbs, paste and 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese and spoon on top.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper until well blended.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients except grated cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350°.
After cooking a while, sprinkle cheese all over top and punch in with fork.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and continue to bake.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: beef enchilada rice
directions: Brown beef in oil in skillet.
Add onion and saute with beef until tender.
Add garlic, saute 15 seconds.
Add chili powder, oregano, tomatoes with juice, salt and water.
Break up tomatoes and bring to a
boil.
Add rice.
Stir, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Place cheese strips on top.
Replace cover.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes, until cheese has melted.
Serve. Makes 4 servings, less than 350 calories.

title: baked flounder
directions: Lay the fish fillets in a greased baking dish (use flounder or any other fish of choice).
Thin the soup with the milk.
Pour over fish and bake in the oven for approximately 20 minutes at 400°.
Just before serving, sprinkle the onion rings over the fish.
Place back in the oven to brown for 3 to 4 minutes (set timer).

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream well together the butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Add flour and mix well.
Pat into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake until golden, about 18 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
While warm, sprinkle with chocolate chips on top.
Place in the oven 1 minute, then spread melted chocolate over all. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: tropical fruit pops
directions: Combine bananas, pineapple, strawberries, yogurt and honey in a blender or food processor.
Whirl until smooth.
Fill 6 ounce paper drinking cups or plastic juice pop holders with mixture.
Place a wooden stick in each and freeze.

title: applets
directions: Soak Knox gelatine with 1 cup applesauce.
In a large kettle combine 1 1/2 cups applesauce, sugar, salt and lemon juice; bring to a boil.
Add gelatine mixture and boil for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool.
Add walnuts, orange extract and vanilla extract. Mix well and pour into well-greased 8 x 13-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.
Let stand in open awhile to let edges dry.
Can also use pureed strawberries, pears or apricots.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from candy and set aside. In large bowl, beat shortening and peanut butter until well blended.
Add 1/3 cup white sugar and 1/3 cup brown sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well. Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to peanut mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately place chocolate piece on top of each cookie, pressing down so cookie cracks around edges.
Cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Heat all ingredients over medium-low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and store in jar in refrigerator.
Use on pancakes or desserts.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: In heavy saucepan stir together 2/3 c. sugar, cornstarch and salt, 3 beaten egg yolks, slightly stir into sugar mixture with sour cream. Cook and stir constantly over low heat until thickened. Stir in raisins and cool. Pour into baked shell, beat egg whites until frothy, slowly beat in 1/3 c. remaining sugar 1 tsp at a time. Continue incresing speed till stiff peaks form, spread on pie and brown. Serve as soon as possible.

title: strawberry cream layered salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mash bananas and combine with thawed strawberries and their juice, pineapple and nuts.
Add gelatin mixture.

Pour half the mixture into an 8-inch square baking dish; cover and chill until firm (about 1 1/2 hours). Cover remaining gelatin mixture and let stand at room temperature. When refrigerated portion is firm, spread evenly with sour cream. Spoon remaining gelatin mixture evenly over cream layer.
Cover and chill until firm (at least 4 hours).
May be cut into squares and served on lettuce or made in a pretty clear bowl and passed.

title: blueberry swirl
directions: In a large bowl, begin layering:
layer of chipped up graham crackers, layer of Eagle Brand milk (mixed with lemon juice), blueberries and Cool Whip (beaten together with milk).
Repeat using half of the ingredients each time and ending with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with egg mixture. Add vanilla and zucchini.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in 2 loaf pans.
Add pecans or coconut if you would like.

title: terri and margot's cake(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Follow the directions on the box.
When it says "eggs" you add actual egg whites or Egg Beaters or any other brand.
When it says "oil" you use pureed prunes in the same volume.
tags: cake mix which calls for oil

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces and place in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise; mix and spread over top as you would frost a cake.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
You may garnish with additional bacon and parsley, if desired.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Fry hamburger; keep stirring at first to get it to separate. Fry enough to get grease out and drain it.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Stir in all ingredients except cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top last 15 minutes.

title: beer n' cheese
directions: Beat Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and butter in food processor or mixer until smooth.
Gradually add beer and mustard. Refrigerate until stiff enough to be rolled into a ball, approximately 2 hours.
(In the meantime, drink the rest of the beer.)
Roll into a ball and place in the bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until just before serving.
Chop parsley very fine and roll cheese ball in parsley.
Serve with crackers or French bread.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beans about 1/2 hour.
Drain and rinse.
Put in roasting pan or casserole; add all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven, covered, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sesame salmon boats
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove skin, if desired.
Mash bones.
Halve avocado; remove seed.
Place each half on a salad plate lined with crisp salad greens.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine mayonnaise, dill weed, garlic salt and 1 teaspoon of sesame seed. Fold in salmon and mashed bones.
Spoon in avocado halves. Sprinkle with remaining sesame seed to serve.
Makes two servings.

title: alma's easy baked beans
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Saute the onions in bacon fat. Brown the smoked sausage in bacon fat.
Heat together mustard, salt, pepper, vinegar and brown sugar until sugar dissolves.
Mix all the ingredients together and simmer in a large pot on top of the stove for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or simmer in crock-pot for several hours.

title: apple pie(kansas city)
directions: Cut apples; place in unbaked pie crust.
Mix dry ingredients and pour over apples.
Pour orange juice and lemon juice over top. Put butter on top.
Add pie crust on top; brush on milk and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dijon chicken drummettes
directions: Cover a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan with foil and spray lightly with vegetable cooking spray.
In small bowl, stir together Miracle Whip, mustard and onion.

Brush each drummette with Miracle Whip mixture and then roll in cheese bread crumbs. Layer in single layer in prepared pan and sprinkle with pepper. Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until chicken is brown.
Makes 20.

title: pineapple fruit dip
directions: Cream sugar, egg and juice. Mix flour in well.
Bring to boil, let it cool and add Cool Whip.

title: orange tea cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add yogurt and Egg Beaters. Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Combine orange juice concentrate, water and orange rind.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and orange juice mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto slightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Quickly remove from baking sheet.
When cool, frost.

title: strawberry-yogurt dip
directions: Whip strawberries in blender until smooth.
Add yogurt and mix until well blended.
Serve with Fruit Dunkers.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form meatballs and put a cube of cheese inside each one.
Cook on medium heat in slow cooker for one hour and switch to low until done.
Serve over rice.

title: refrigerator fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, sugar and evaporated milk in double boiler. Pour hot mixture over rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Press firmly in pan and store for 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: the really great bean salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and combine in a large bowl.
Mix sugar with vinegar; add oil and seasonings and pour over vegetables. Stir well and refrigerate overnight.
Stir several times to marinate.
Drain before serving.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: potato-broccoli bake
directions: Melt the 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk; cook and stir until bubbly.
Add cheeses, stirring until melted.
Stir in potatoes.
Turn half the mixture into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish; top with broccoli. Spoon remaining mixture over top.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Mix crumbs and remaining butter; sprinkle around edges.
Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in a pan.
Cook rapidly until the temperature reaches 300°.
Add food coloring and flavoring.
Pour onto cookie sheet; let it set to harden.
Cover with powdered sugar.
To crack candy, use butter knife handle.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well to blend; use as a dip for vegetables.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add a little cream to make paste.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Add milk to flour, cocoa and sugar and stir. Beat egg yolks. Add 1/2 cup milk, then 2 cups milk. Beat all ingredients together. Cook over double boiler. Stir until thick. Add margarine and vanilla. Use egg whites and make meringue. Beat with sugar until stiff. Put pudding in souffle dish and add meringue. Bake at 300° until meringue is done.

title: piccalilli
directions: Chop the cabbage, tomatoes, red and green peppers and onions. Mix with the salt; let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain and press in cloth to remove all liquid possible.
Boil vinegar, water, sugar and spices for 5 minutes.
Add the chopped vegetable mixture; bring to a boil.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Makes 3 qts. in casserol sizes you choose Boil, pick and cut chicken to desired size.
Saute vegetables in 1 1/3c. water plus butter and lightly toss with Pepperidge Farm's Stuffing.
Gently press 1/2 of stuffing mix in bottom of casseroles, top with chicken, add chicken gravy and top with remaining stuffing.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
Reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Add flour and egg to salmon.
Add salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
Add baking powder to reserved liquid.
Beat well until foamy.
Pour into salmon mixture and blend well.
Fry in hot oil; they brown very fast.
Drain on paper towels.

title: squash pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over squash; let stand for 1 hour.
Drain through colander; do not rinse.
While squash is standing, chop onions and peppers; set aside.
When squash has been drained, bring vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed to a boil.
Add squash, onions and peppers.
Bring to a boil again; boil 15 minutes.
Put in jars.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Place slices of angel food cake around punch bowl.
Make vanilla pudding with milk.
Place pineapple, cherry pie filling and chopped pecans in layers using each twice.
Cover with Cool Whip and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.
Best if set overnight before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach to drain (I use cheesecloth).
Mix all ingredients; refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
To serve, cut off top of unsliced wheat or rye bread.
Scoop out inside; fill with dip mixture.
(Bread insides can be cut into squares and served as dippers.)

title: luscious lemon creme fruit dip
directions: In a bowl beat eggs and add 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice. Beat together.
In a saucepan put 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch. Stir in water.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Beat in egg mixture.
Cook on low heat.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Add vanilla and cool completely.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: stew from the wild
directions: Cut meat into chunks; roll in flour mixed with next 4 ingredients.
Brown in butter.
Add mushroom soup; warm and stir together, about 15 minutes.
Great with squirrel, venison and duck too.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Pour over cake mixture and bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crowd-pleaser cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and set aside.
In a frying pan, brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add onion, celery, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
If mixture is to be made a while before serving, add the avocado seeds to help keep it from darkening.
Refrigerate.
Serve.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Bring to full rolling boil and pour over bread.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Make a crust of confectioners sugar, margarine and flour. Spread on a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool. Blend the cream cheese, vanilla, milk and lemon juice and spread over the crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Arrange cut fruit in design over the top.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut in wedge-shaped pieces.

title: cherry nut ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in freezer.
Add milk to full line.

title: strawberry deluscious
directions: Place strawberries, lemon juice, sugar and egg white in mixing bowl.
Beat on low for 1 minute.
Beat on high for 3 minutes until thick and fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze in 8 x 8-inch pan for 2 hours.

title: easy and quick pizza dough
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup of the flour, yeast and salt. Add water and oil.
Beat until well blended, a couple of minutes with mixer at low speed.
Stir in remaining flour gradually, to make a firm dough.
Knead dough on a floured surface 10 to 12 times.
Or do it my way and knead it right in the bowl.
Cover; let it rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Makes two 12-inch pizza crusts.
Grease pans first.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes (begins to brown).
Top with sauce and your favorite toppings and bake 10 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, chocolate squares and sugar.
Melt slowly and mix well.
A double boiler keeps this from sticking.
Add vanilla. Sift together salt, flour and baking powder.
Add to oil mixture and blend together well.
Chill several hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 350°. Roll a spoonful of cookie mix in the powdered sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: blueberry sky pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy; add lemonade and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Fold in 3/4 of whipped cream and 2/3 of the pie filling.
Put in pie crusts.
Top with blueberries and whipped cream.

title: chicken breast royal
directions: Cut beef in small pieces and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll chicken breasts, tucking in any loose pieces to smooth. Wrap tightly with bacon strip.
Place on top of beef.
Blend sour cream and soup and spoon over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: saganaki(fried cheese)
directions: Heat butter in a large frying pan until melted and foam has subsided.
Beat egg and flour together.
Dip cheese slices in egg mixture and fry until well browned on both sides.
Pour brandy over
the
cheese
in
the skillet and ignite.
Squeeze lemon juice over the cheese until flame subsides.

title: snake alley noodles
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Keep warm.
Combine soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and 1 cup water.
Set aside.
Cook pork with ginger, garlic and red pepper.
Add green onions.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add soy sauce mixture.
Cook and stir until boils and thickens.
Add shrimp.
Heat.
Toss over noodles.

title: busy day stew
directions: In crock-pot, turned on low, put in stew meat, vegetables and the soups, no water. Cook for 8 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: That's something I'm able to toss with the best, all over the table, the floor and the guest!

title: pineapple squares
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and oleo. Add flour.

Mix well and roll into ball. Wrap in wax paper. Chill 4 hours or overnight. Divide dough in half. Roll one piece to fit bottom of medium size cookie sheet. Spread with cool filling. Roll rest of dough and place on top of filling, sealing edges by pressing around edges of pan. Prick top full of holes and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Add all ingredients in baking dish.
Add enough milk to make it soupy.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; stir in milk a small amount at a time. Blend in vanilla and salt.
Mixture may be slightly dry.
Coat each cherry with mixture.
Dip cherries in mixture.
Place on wax paper with toothpick to harden.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: econo cocoa mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together real well and store in large container.
Add 2 heaping tablespoons to a cup of boiling water and stir well.
Add marshmallows for extra taste.

title: apricot salad
directions: Add boiling water to
jello
and
1 cup pineapple juice from crushed pineapple.
Let jello set, not solid, just loose, and then whip in the
cream
cheese,
Cool
Whip,
celery
and pineapple. Garnish with nuts and chill.

title: cold salmon foam
directions: Drain the salmon and look it over carefully for bones and bits of skin.
Using a fork, crumble it in a mixing bowl.
Add the oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper.
Beat them into the salmon until you've obtained a smooth, evenly blended mixture.

title: apricot bread
directions: Pour water over apricots.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugar to beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in nuts.
Add apricots to dry ingredients.
Stir in egg mixture.
Stir in shortening and vanilla.
Bake in 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for one hour at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, butter and confectioners sugar.
Press in ungreased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch), building up a 1/2-inch edge.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients, about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake about 25 minutes longer or until imprint remains when touched lightly in center. Cool and cut.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw shell
at room temperature for 20 minutes. Mix broccoli with soup, egg and cheese.
Pour into shell. Sprinkle with crumbs and almonds.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Great luncheon or supper dish.
Can be prepared with other frozen cooked or canned vegetables such as carrots, limas, celery, green beans, peas, cauliflower, etc.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: caribbean grilled turkey
directions: To outdoor grill, lightly spray unheated grill rack with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare grill for medium direct heat cooking.
In food processor or blender, puree preserves, green onions, garlic, hot pepper sauce, pepper, salt, lime juice, lime peel and soy sauce.
Spread tenderloins with the puree.
Place tenderloins on rack over medium hot grill.
Turn frequently for even cooking and browning.
Cook tenderloins for about 20 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.

title: paula's bread
directions: Knead dough.
Let rise in large bowl covered with a lid or towel until double size (in a warm place).
Shape into desired shapes.
Let rise about one hour.
Bake at 375° until brown.
You can make rolls, hamburger buns or hot dog buns.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: Saute oleo or butter, onion and garlic.
Add zucchini and cook until soft.
Put in blender and add remaining ingredients;
blend on high until smooth.
Add salt to taste.
Serve heated or cold.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers crosswise in even slices.
Soak in lime for 24 hours in 2 gallons of water.
Drain cucumbers.
Wash in clean water.
Soak 4 hours.
Change water every hour for four hours. The last time drain on towel.
Do not drain in silk. Bring to boil sugar, vinegar and pickling spice.
Pour over pickles.
Let set overnight.
Next morning, bring to boil until clear (about 35 minutes).
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: peach dump
directions: Drain pineapple.
Put in bottom of baking dish.
Pour cans of peaches on top of pineapple.
Pour dry yellow cake mix on peaches. Pour melted margarine on dry cake mix.
Pour pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli rice quiche
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients and fill rice shell.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, cheese and Bac*Os.
Mix dressing and pour over mixture.
Toss well.
Chill before serving.

title: stuffed hamburgers(microwave)
directions: Shape beef into 8 thin patties.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place selected filling over 4 patties and top with other 4 patties.
Seal fillings inside by pinching firmly around edges. Put into microwave dish; cover with wax paper and microwave at High 7 to 9 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 4 minutes.

title: pot roast of beef(slow cooker)
directions: Put half of vegetables on bottom.
Salt and pepper meat and put in crock-pot.
Add rest of vegetables and liquid.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in order given and sprinkle with Bac*Os or bacon.
When ready to serve, put on a bed of lettuce.

title: soap crayons
directions: In a bowl, put water (add color to the water), then add soap flakes.
Mix until thick and no lumps.
Press the mixture tightly into the cubes of an ice tray.
Let the tray sit in a warm, dry place for several days or until hard.
Pop them out and they are ready to use on anything washable (sink, tub or countertop).

title: pineapple crowned sausage patties(serves 50)
directions: Mix all ingredients except sausage and pineapple in large bowl, add sausage and mix well.
Shape meat mixture in 5 ounce oval patties about 1-inch thick.
Place in single layers on greased baking sheet.
Top each patty with pineapple slice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: famous bread pudding
directions: Mix Half and Half, whipping cream, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Arrange bread on bottom of 10 x 12 pan.
Pour mixture over bread. Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over top.
Spread raisins on top and cover with foil.
Bake in water bath at 400 degrees for 75-90 minutes.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp in simmering salted water 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Peel and clean.

title: antipasto from rosemary's kitchen
directions: Combine olive oil, vinegar, ketchup and chili sauce and simmer about 30 minutes to remove ketchup taste.
Add cauliflower, peppers and onions and simmer 10 minutes.
Add beans, mushrooms, olives and pickles and bring to a boil.
Add tuna and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove, cool and place in containers for freezing or seal in jars.
Makes a great Christmas gift!!!

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough; do not let rise. Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix together melted butter, brown sugar, milk and cinnamon. Pour 1/3 of caramel mixture into the pan.
Cut or tear bread dough into walnut size pieces and place in pan.
Pour remaining caramel on top.
Let rise. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool 5 to 10 minutes and invert on tray.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put butter, oil, cocoa and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Sift together flour and sugar.
Pour chocolate over dry ingredients and mix well.
Then add buttermilk, baking soda, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased broiler pan or jelly roll pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
While hot, frost.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Combine syrup, margarine and brown sugar in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until syrupy.
Do not boil!
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (glass preferred).
Layer bread over syrup.
Beat together until foamy eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour over bread.
Cover pan with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Remove foil to bake. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, let set 5 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares and serve.
May be topped with strawberries, blueberries or other fresh fruit. Doesn't need syrup or butter.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter in a 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring occasionally until onions are tender and just begin to brown.
Sprinkle with flour; gradually stir in one can of broth.
Heat to boiling; stir constantly.
Stir in remaining broth, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Place 1 slice of toast in each of 6 heatproof bowls; pour soup over toast.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil soups with tops 3 to 4 inches from heat until cheese is melted and light brown, about 5 minutes.

title: mrs. barkley's baked crabmeat
directions: Make thick cream sauce as follows:
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour, add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Season with salt, onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire, parsley, red pepper and celery salt.
Add eggs, unbeaten, and stir, but do not boil.
Mix well with crabmeat.
Place in Pyrex dish.
Cover with crumbs, dot with butter.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
(I always add a little more "dashes" of all seasonings.)
Just taste and season.

title: marinade sauce
directions: Marinate sliced meat a minimum of 1 hour before preparing to stir-fry, grill, bake, etc.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar over chops and place a slice of onion on each.
Mix together ketchup and water; pour over chops.
Pour lemon juice over chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, covered.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add rest of ingredients, except pecans. Mix together.
Chill enough to shape into 2 balls or logs.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1 cup of juice.
Combine all fruit in a large bowl; toss gently.
Combine pudding and juice in a large mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit and toss gently.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine egg yolks with milk and mix well.
Add lime juice a little at a time and stir until filling is smooth and creamy. Pour into the crust and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Chill.
Just before serving, top with whipped cream and garnish with a twist of lime.

title: lemon chess bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and spread in bottom of greased 11 x 16-inch sheet cake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after cooked.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook tomato sauce, brown sugar and butter 5 minutes.
Place bread in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour tomato sauce mix over bread.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
(May be prepared ahead of time.)

title: sunshine souffle
directions: Separate eggs.
Prepare white sauce by melting margarine in a saucepan.
Stir in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and cayenne until smooth.
Gradually add milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer until sauce is thick and leaves the bottom of the pan.
Blend in the Parmesan and Cheddar cheeses. With a wire whisk, beat egg yolks and add to the cheese mixture.

title: swedish meatball sauce
directions: Mix both ingredients in a pot on medium heat. Add to meatballs.

title: cabbage and white bean soup
directions: Heat oil and butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion; saute 3 minute.
Add carrots and celery; saute 3 minutes. Add caraway seed; cook, stirring 1 minute.
Stir in cabbage, water and sugar.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes with juice, breaking up tomatoes with wooden spoon.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add beans and vinegar.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes or until heated through.
Stir in parsley, if you wish.

title: venison roast
directions: Season roast with salt.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet. Add other ingredients.
Place in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low or in 350° oven for 3 hours.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt together the margarine, cocoa, peanut butter and vanilla. Bring just to boiling point around the edge.
Put in a bowl and add powdered sugar; mix thoroughly.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan. Press out evenly.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: maple acorn squash tart
directions: Peel squash; cut of both ends.
Cut squash in half crosswise and then in half lengthwise to make quarters; discard seeds.
Slice each quarter crosswise into 1/4-inch thick pieces.

title: grilled zucchini
directions: Place aluminum foil on grill.
Turn edges up to catch sauce. Light grill, run it on low.
Put 1 tablespoon butter on foil wherever you plan to place a zucchini.
Add 1/4 teaspoon (more or less) chopped garlic to each "spot".
Add 1 tablespoon brown sugar and salt and pepper to each "spot".

title: man in the moon cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy bread
directions: Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Mix cheese and butter.
Soften onion flakes in water; drain and stir into cheese mixture.
Spread on the cut bread surfaces.
Reassemble loaf and wrap in foil.
Refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.
Heat in a 400° oven until cheese is melted, approximately 25 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: In skillet, add hamburger, diced onion and salt.
Cook until done.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and taco sauce.
Use a regular cake square pan.
Crush nacho chips in the bottom of pan.
Pour hamburger mixture on top of chips.
Then pour cheese on top of hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Cut into squares.
Top with diced tomatoes, olives and sour cream.

title: cheeseless cheesecake
directions: Place the following ingredients in a blender for 2 minutes: crushed pineapple, unflavored gelatin, boiling water and pineapple juice.
Add the following ingredients to the blender and blend on high speed for 3 minutes:
lemon juice, vanilla, artificial sweetener, dry milk and rest of pineapple juice.
Pour into pie pan or 4 dessert dishes and refrigerate.
Makes 4 servings with each serving equaling 1 cup of skim milk and 1 fruit.
Enjoy!

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: To make sauce, combine chicken soup, milk, cheese, chicken, mushrooms, wine, celery, pimentos, olives, salt and pepper in large pot.
Pour over cooked spaghetti and stir through. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, in casserole for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: yellow squash stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, saute the squash and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Transfer to a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into an 8-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: easter braid
directions: Food processor method:
Place flour, sugar, salt and baking soda in bowl.
Process 3 seconds.
Stir yeast with 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 1 tablespoon of water to a smooth mixture and let proof. Melt butter and let cool.
Put the eggs, butter and buttermilk on top of dry ingredients.
Process a few seconds.
Add proofed yeast. Process 30 seconds.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic clove.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, oregano and chili powder.
Alternate layers of meat, beans and chips, ending with chips.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake last 10 minutes.
Top with shredded lettuce.

title: easiest barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a quart jar.
Shake well and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and let stand with sugar on them for 1 hour.
Dissolve jello in water as instructed on the package.
Add all the ingredients.
Mold and serve with whipped cream or salad dressing.
(One pound of cranberries equals 2 cups.)

title: strawberry-lime jam
directions: Sterilize 4 half-pint (8 ounce) jars and lids, following manufacturer's directions.

title: champagne punch
directions: Chill all the ingredients.
Pour into punch bowl.
Slice lemonade.
Add ice last.
Garnish with orange slices with cherry on 1/2 toothpick.
If sweeter punch desired, add 1 tablespoon powdered sugar at a time until taste as desired.

title: broccoli-cheese squares
directions: Grease
a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with the margarine.
Steam broccoli until partially cooked, about 3 minutes.
Cool and press dry.
Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Thoroughly mix flour, baking powder and salt; stir into egg mixture, mixing well.
Fold in broccoli, cheese and onion; spoon into baking dish, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 35 minutes or until set and lightly browned. Let stand 5 minutes, then cut into bite-size pieces.
Makes 4 dozen 1 1/2-inch squares.
Great for showers or parties.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Melt butter, add cocoa and cola, heat to boiling. Cool slightly. Pour over flour and sugar mixture, stir until well blended. Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda and vanilla. Mix well, stir in marshmallows. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Frost while hot.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk in a large bowl.
Stir in Cool Whip with pudding.
Line oblong pan with graham crackers.
Spread pudding and Cool Whip mixture of top of crackers.
Alternate again, ending with graham crackers on top.
Spread chocolate icing on top of crackers and refrigerate overnight.

title: salad supreme spaghetti
directions: Boil, rinse and cool the spaghetti.
Add to it cut up tomatoes, green pepper, green onions, grated Cheddar cheese, pepperoni, McCormick Salad Supreme seasoning and an oil and vinegar Italian dressing.
Chill overnight.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Bring brown sugar, butter and milk to a simmer. Cook until soft ball appears to form when a small amount is dropped in cold water. Remove from heat and beat until spreading consistency.

title: 1-2-3 apple pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients until moist.
Place in buttered 10 inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done. Serves 8 to 10.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly with a spoon.
Place in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and level.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Serves 8.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add other ingredients and pour over ice.
Serves 50.

title: tuscan bean dip
directions: In food processor, process garlic, onion and parsley until finely chopped.
Add beans, lemon juice, pepper and salt.
Process until smooth.
Stir in pimentos.
Refrigerate if not serving immediately.
Serve with crackers, pita slices, toasted bread or veggies.

title: rusty's red beans and rice
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion in small amount of oil.
Add pinto beans, picante sauce, salt and sausage.
Bring to a boil, then cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked rice and serve.

title: best french coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Turn oven to 300° and bake until brown and firm, approximately 40 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350.

title: amazing apple cake(apple cake squares)
directions: Mix butter or margarine with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Mix flour and baking powder with eggs and butter mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Roll one half onto cookie sheet.
Slice apples. Place onto dough and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Add raisins and nuts.
Roll other half of dough on aluminum foil to fit on top of cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: june's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (do not add salt to water).
Cool and debone. Grate or dice carrots, celery and onion.
Boil until soft.
Beat egg.
Mix with drained carrots, celery and onion.
Melt butter and cube bread.
Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Mix 1 cup broth (made from cooking chicken) with soup.
(If you don't have enough broth to make 1 cup, add juice from boiling carrots.)

title: hrustuli(a yugoslavian pastry)
directions: Heat the milk and butter to hot in a pot.
Mix the eggs, sugar, vanilla, baking powder and salt in a bowl and beat well.
Add hot milk with butter to the mixture.
Beat well.
Add the flour.
Add enough where dough gets thick.
Knead dough.
Roll into long rolls and cut 4 to 5 pieces to each roll.
Roll out each section, dusting with flour, flat.
Cut strips and make into bows.
Fry in Wesson oil.
Remove and put in bowl and sprinkle with sugar when hot.
A pastry treat; you can't eat just one!

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop all vegetables; set aside.
Place sugar and vinegar (use equal amounts, 1 cup sugar to 1 cup vinegar) in large kettle. Bring to boil.
Add turmeric (1 teaspoon).
Add chopped vegetables.
Make sure you mix enough sugar and vinegar to cover vegetables.
Bring back to rolling boil.
Pack in jars and seal. Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Good with soup beans.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together the sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in beans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm or chilled with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: glazed applesauce cookies
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients until smooth.
Sift flour with soda. Add 1/2 of the flour to shortening mixture and blend.
Stir in fruit, nuts and applesauce.
Add rest of flour and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls and spread out a little, they do not spread themselves.
Bake at 400° for 11 to 14 minutes.
While still hot, spread with thin coating of glaze.

title: delicious apple pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter and pack in dish for crust.
Mix sour cream, milk and lemon juice and pour on top.
Spread pie filling on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Then put walnuts and cinnamon on top.

title: poached quail and apples
directions: Chop apples, mushrooms, onion and garlic; mix and fill cavity of quail.
Combine flour, salt and m.s.g. in bowl.
Wet quail and dredge in flour mixture to coat birds.
In a deep skillet melt butter and add cider and wine.
Place quail in skillet and simmer 1 hour or until done.
Remove quail and add apple butter to thicken drippings to make gravy.
Serve on a bed of wild rice and garnish with apple slices and mushrooms.

title: christmas tea cakes
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Flatten bread with rolling pin. Thoroughly combine cream cheese and egg yolk.
Spread bread slices with cream cheese mixture and roll up jelly-roll style.
After spreading and rolling all 20 slices of bread, cut each roll in half making 40 blintzes.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip blintzes in butter to coat and roll in sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with sour cream decorated with fresh parsley.
Blintzes can be frozen and thawed before baking.

title: cocktail winnies
directions: Put all ingredients in slow cooker.
Stir well and let cook on High heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix and shape into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. May refrigerate before baking or freeze for future use.
Can freeze after baking.

title: "pot roast" meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, milk, crumbs, ketchup, sauce, salt and pepper. Shape into loaf.
Place in center of pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Place vegetables in layers around meat.
Sprinkle each layer with parsley flakes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
(Cover tightly with foil before cooking.)
Uncover and brown meat.

title: okra, corn and tomatoes
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Add tomatoes and cook about 10 minutes.
Add layer of okra, then layer of corn.
Do not stir at this point.
Cover with lid and cook about 20 minutes.
Remove lid and stir.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: parmesan salad
directions: Cut or break cauliflower and broccoli into bite-size pieces; thinly slice stems.
Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onions, and 3/4 of the bacon bits.
Toss well.
Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and sugar in small bowl.
Toss with salad just before serving.

title: a happy life
directions: Mix these thoroughly.
Add tears of joy and sadness and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little gifts of love.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith to lighten the other ingredients and raise texture to great heights of living.
After pouring all this into your daily life, bake well with the heat of human kindness. Serve with a generous smile!

title: country pie crust
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt together.
Cut butter and lard into flour until mixture resembles crumbs.
Add water and mix until mixture comes away from bowl.
Sometimes you may have to add more water.
Roll out on floured surface.

title: fig preserves
directions: Add sugar and lemon juice to hot water.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Add figs and cook rapidly for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Add sliced lemons and continue cooking rapidly until figs are clear, about 10 to 15 minutes.
(If syrup becomes too thick before figs become clear, add boiling water, 1/4 cup at a time.)
Cover and let stand 12 to 24 hours in a cool place.
Pack into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch head space. Adjust caps.
Process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 10 half-pints.

title: candy turtles
directions: Melt caramels; add cream and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Let set.
When cool, drip on chocolate.

title: cheese balls
directions: With your fingers, mix cheese, flour, butter and just enough water to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough into small (3/4 inch) balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° until lightly brown (about 15 minutes).

title: bulgoki(korean)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let marinate until needed (doesn't have to marinate long).
Cook in pan until done - add water to make more sauce.
Cornstarch can be added to thicken the sauce. Serve over rice or noodles

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and put in Dixie cups and freeze.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes in oven until done, then remove and cool thoroughly.
Remove insides with spoon (you can save this for mashed potatoes).
Leave small layer of potatoes; deep fry until crisp.
Cut bacon into small bits and microwave until crunchy. Add cheese and bacon to potatoes.
Top with sour cream and scallions or chives.

title: martha's almond bark coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and roll into small balls; put in refrigerator until cold, then dip in almond bark.

title: basic fish stock
directions: Combine all ingredients with water and cook for 1/2 hour.
Add fish heads and bones (about 1 pound) and simmer for 15 more minutes.
Strain.
Makes 2 quarts.
Fresh stock will keep for 3 days or may be frozen for future use.

title: french bread
directions: Cool boiling water and butter until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water with sugar added.
Combine yeast mixture with water mixture.
Pour liquid mixture in large mixing bowl and stir in 3 cups flour and salt gradually.
Then add 1 1/2 cups flour by hand and knead 1 minute.
Put in a greased bowl with lid and let rise 1 1/2 hours or until doubled; divide in two parts and form loaves long and thin.
Place on cookie sheet and let rise 30 minutes.
Before baking, beat 1 egg white and 1 teaspoon cold water and glaze bread loaves.
Seeds may be added on top of loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and sounds hollow when tapped with knife.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: hot fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in medium saucepan, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, making sure all flour is mixed.
Add eggs, margarine, vanilla and milk.
Pour into 9-inch uncooked pie shell and bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: delicious microwave chili
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Cover with glass lid.
Microwave for about 5 minutes on High or until meat is browned.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Re-cover.
Microwave for 14 to 16 minutes on Medium or until hot.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with shredded cheese on top.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In saucepan, combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, celery seed, garlic and bay leaves.
Bring to boiling; simmer 30 minutes. Cool.
Pour over eggs in crock, glass jar or bowl.
Cover; refrigerate for 2 to 3 days.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in large casserole.
Pour all but 1 cup of stuffing evenly over margarine.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of this. Add onion and celery.
Spread can of chicken soup (undiluted) on top of this.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on this. Pour 2 1/2 cups of chicken broth on top and bake for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Put beans in casserole dish.
Chip up bacon.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour mixture over beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: basic muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Use only enough milk to make desired consistency. Pour batter in muffin pan and bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt margarine; stir in peanut butter, then add powdered sugar.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler and pour over the mixture.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours; cut at room temperature.
These taste like Reese's peanut butter cups.

title: pumpkin bread #1
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375°. Makes 2 loaves.
May be frozen.

title: angus fancy onions
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden brown.
Transfer to a casserole dish.
Combine the bread crumbs, salt, pepper and mustard.
Spread over onions in the casserole.
Sprinkle the cheese over mixture.
Bake until cheese is melted, about 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chimis by lori
directions: Combine chicken, picante sauce, onion, cumin, oregano and salt in saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes or until liquid has evaporated. Brush one side of tortilla with butter.
Spoon about 1/3 cup meat mixture onto center of unbuttered side.
Top with 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Fold 2 sides over filling.
Fold ends down.

title: putting on the ritz
directions: In top of double boiler, combine chopped dates and sweetened condensed milk; stir together until smooth.
After water boils, cook approximately 10 minutes, stirring mixture until is is smooth and thickens; cool; add chopped nuts and mix well.
Spread a spoonful of mixture on Ritz crackers.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 8 minutes.
Cool well.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in rectangular baking dish. Top with crackers.
Pour margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pan sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add salt, soda, vanilla, milk and flour.
Spread on lightly greased cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar.
Add crushed crackers.
Mix in nuts, baking powder and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mrs. kinney's sponge cake
directions: Sift flour, then measure and sift again with salt and baking powder.
Beat the egg whites until quite stiff, then add 1/2 cup sugar to the whites, 2 tablespoons at a time.
The egg yolks are then beaten until thick and lemon colored and 1/3 cup sugar is added and beaten into the yolks.
Fold egg whites and yolk mixture together.
Add the vanilla and sift the dry ingredients into the egg mixture.
Mix.

Bake in a 4 1/2 x 10-inch tube cake pan which is ungreased in a preheated oven of 325° for 40 to 50 minutes. When done, it should be turned upside down and allowed to hang until nearly cold before removing from the pan.

title: pop-up rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Melt a pat of butter in each muffin tin. Fill cups 1/2 to 3/4 full of dough.
Bake at 350° until brown. Makes 6 to 8.

title: shrimp aspic salad
directions: Boil bay and celery leaves in V-8 juice for 5 minutes; strain and discard leaves.
Dilute gelatin in water and add to hot juice. Quickly whisk until well dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well and pour into a glass baking dish.
Chill until set.

title: sweet potato-berry bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place sweet potatoes in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with berries and nuts.
Dot with marmalade. Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: caramel chocolate brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler, stirring until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, melted butter, remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Press half of cake mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top, then cover evenly with caramel mixture.
Crumble remaining cake mixture on top.
Bake 20 minutes. Cool 30 minutes.
Chill 1 hour before cutting into squares. Yield:
48 brownies.

title: chicken-pork loaf
directions: Grind the chicken meat and pork with the onions, garlic, tomatoes and bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly the salt, egg, ground pepper and milk, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Pack a well-greased loaf pan or Pyrex casserole.
Steam or bake for 1 hour at 350° or until loaf is firm.
Serve whole or sliced.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate overnight.

title: soft molasses gingerbread
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, baking soda, sugar and ginger together. Add shortening, beaten egg and molasses.
Add boiling water last. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dad's favorite beef rolls(rinderrouladen)
directions: Lay steaks on flat surface.
Spread each with mustard; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Divide pickles, bacon and onion among the steaks.
Roll up steaks jelly roll fashion; secure with toothpicks or thread.
Brown steak rolls in saucepan.
Pour in beef broth, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove beef rolls and put aside.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with glaze.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together in a baking dish.

title: low-fat cherry chip cake
directions: Mix cherry Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water; set aside.
Mix egg whites, 1/3 cup water and drained pineapple (save juice).
Mix with cherry chip cake mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (lightly greased) at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Let cool and take a toothpick and punch holes all over the top; pour saved pineapple juice all over the top and let soak about 5 minutes.
Cover with whipped topping and spread evenly the pie filling over whipped topping.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: pizza dip
directions: Layer in pie plate in this order: cream cheese, sour cream, pizza sauce, oregano, pepper, garlic powder and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
I serve this dip with nacho chips.

title: pie crust
directions: Take 1/3 cup flour from the 2 cups flour and add cold water. Make a paste. In a separate bowl, mix the remaining flour, shortening and salt together until mixture forms small peas. Add the paste and mix a little, then roll out dough. Put in pie plates.

title: lemon pudding pound cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored (5 to 8 minutes). Beat in cake mix, dry pudding, water and oil.
Continue beating at medium speed 10 minutes.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan with removable bottom.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove hot cake from the pan shell, but leave on tube and bottom.
Prick holes over top and sides.
Drizzle glaze over top and sides.
Cool cake on tube of pan (preferably overnight).
Run knife between tube and cake.
Turn cake out on hand and turn over on plate.

title: biscuit brownies
directions: Melt in microwave the chocolate chips and butter, then add Eagle Brand milk, egg and Bisquick.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes. Frost with 1 can chocolate fudge frosting.
You may microwave frosting 45 seconds to soften.

title: rice and tuna pie
directions: Combine rice, butter, 1 egg, 1 tablespoon onion and 1/4 tsp. marjoram.
Press onto bottom and sides of lightly buttered 10-inch pie plate or 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle tuna evenly over rice shell.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over tuna.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: going over the hill
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in peas and sausage.
In a separate cup, mix flour and water.
Stir until thin (adding water as needed).
Stir flour mixture into peas and sausage.
Add pepper and salt.
Let simmer for about one hour.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, brown the meat, celery, onions and green pepper. Pour off the grease. Add tomato products, seasonings and drained and rinsed kidney beans.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Fork prick the kielbasa and boil for about 4 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1/4 inch diagonal slices.
Mix catsup and grape jelly in a saucepan and stir until smooth.
Add lemon juice and kielbasa slices.
Serve with tooth picks.

title: traditional sponge cake
directions: Line 1 loaf pan with wax paper or cookie tin (to use for a jelly roll).

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat in flour.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Roll in small balls and roll dough in 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will puff up and not look exactly done at this time, but they will fall and be a moist, chewy cookie.

title: christmas meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and shape into small meatballs (approximately 28 to 30).
Brown evenly.
Stir until dissolved the cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Add meatballs and simmer 1 hour.
Delicious anytime of the year!

title: carolyn's roasted garlic pork supper
directions: Remove papery outer skin from garlic. (Do not peel or separate cloves.) Cut top off garlic heads, leaving root end intact. Brush with oil. Sprinkle with basil and oregano. Wrap each bulb in heavy-duty foil. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until softened. Cool for 10 to 15 minutes. Squeeze softened garlic into a small bowl. Add lemon juice and mix well. Rub over the roast. Place roast in a shallow roasting pan. Arrange potatoes, carrots and onion around roast. Pour water into the pan. Sprinkle meat and vegetables with salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered. Bake 1 1/2 hours longer or until or until meat thermometer reads 160°. Baste often. Cover and let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: low-fat yogurt
directions: Mix the dry milk and water together and heat to 112°.
Add the yogurt to each quart.
Keep warm until yogurt is made, 3 to 12 hours, depending on temperature.
Don't heat over 115°.

title: baked beans
directions: In a large baking dish, combine beans and Karo.
Cut bacon strips in half and cover beans.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Easy to make for a church supper.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix seasonings and marinate well.
Bake, turning occasionally, at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: plum spice cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add strained plums.
Sift flour and cinnamon together.
Add to mixture, beating well for about 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: tropical pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chops in shallow baking dish. Top with pineapple and orange juice.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together cranberries, sugar, corn syrup and orange juice.
Stirring occasionally, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until cranberry skins pop.
Remove from heat.
Stir in orange sections. Cover; refrigerate several hours.
Just before serving, stir in pecans.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine soup and broth; mix well.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat, add chives, mushrooms and cheese; stir until cheese has melted.
Spoon half the rice into a 3-quart buttered casserole or individual casseroles; top with half the chicken and then half the sauce.
Repeat with remaining rice, chicken and sauce.
Sprinkle pimiento over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scripture cake
directions: You can use 1/2 teaspoon each:
cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon extract.

title: crunchy banana bread
directions: Grease two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 325°. Combine flours, wheat germ, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
In large mixer bowl, with electric mixer on medium, beat eggs with sugar until light and thick.
Beat in mayonnaise.
Alternately beat milk and banana with flour mixture into egg mixture just until moistened.
Fold in 3/4 cup of the coconut and fruit bits.
Pour into loaf pans.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 cup of the remaining coconut.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack after letting cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: pork chop-rice casserole
directions: Place in a baking dish by layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Uncover the last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing.
Mix to blend.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in individual molds or a pan.
Seal and freeze.
Serve before fruits thaw.
Serves 8.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Combine all ingredients except pretzels in a large Ziploc bag. Add pretzels.
Shake.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Bake in a single layer on a cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecued pork
directions: Cut boned pork loin in half lengthwise.
(If tenderloin is thick,
cut it in half and remove membrane.) Mix remaining ingredients, except oil, in a large bowl, stirring until sugar and salt
are	nearly dissolved.
Add pork pieces stirring to coat well.
Marinate
1	hour or more.
Then add 1 tablespoon oil
(to give
pork a shiny glaze.) Marinate at least 3 hours longer or overnight, turning pork occasionally.
Place pork on a
rack
with roasting pan underneath to catch drips.
(Add a small
amount
of water in bottom of the pan for prevent burning.)
Bake
at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 325°
and
continue roasting
to
35 minutes turning pork occasionally.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on low heat for about 1 hour or longer if desired.

title: zucchini rice casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 inch pan with Pam.
Layer zucchini, then cheese.
Sprinkle generously with rice, then with cheese.
Repeat for three layers.
Dilute soup with 1 can of water, mix well and pour over ingredients.
Sprinkle generously with bread crumbs and top with sliced bacon.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour uncovered. Test for doneness.

title: "one pot" dinner in crock-pot(especially for men)
directions: Brown meat in a skillet and put in crock-pot.
Brown onions slightly in skillet.
Add crumbled, cooked bacon, onions and remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Mix well.
Cover and cook on high until heated through.
Reduce to low and cook 4 to 9 hours.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Beat oleo and Crisco for 4 minutes.
Add sugar and beat for 4 more minutes.
Add flour, one tablespoon at a time, and beat into sugar and Crisco mixture.
Add milk and beat for 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and mix well.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in lukewarm water.
Pour boiling water over shortening.
When cool add to the yeast mixture; then add eggs and sugar.
Sift flour and salt together and add to first mixture. Mix
in flour until dough is stiff but still sticky. Turn
dough out on lightly floured surface; knead just enough to handle
good. Place
back into bowl that has been greased. Brush
top
with melted shortening.
Cover and let rise until double.
Make into favorite shape rolls and let rise again.

title: drumstick cake
directions: Mix well the vanilla wafers, peanuts and margarine and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Put the beef in a large boiler and then cover 3/4 of the meat with water.
Add the seasoning that comes with the meat.
Cook on medium heat for 2 hours.
Then add veggies.
Cook until vegetables are tender; about 30 minutes.

title: summer frozen salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sugar in softened cream cheese. Fold in cranberry sauce. Add crushed pineapple and nuts. Add Cool Whip. Freeze at least 6 hours or overnight in a mold or an 8 x 8 pan. Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Add 2 teaspoons to one cup.
Store in refrigerator in an airtight container.

title: bonnie's great dip
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Put in a low dish.
Layer next 5 ingredients.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with corn chips or potato chips.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in glass or plastic container. Place steak in marinade, turning to coat completely.
Marinate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Barbecue or broil until each side is browned on the outside but rare in the center.
Cut steak diagonally across the grain into thin slices.

title: citrus pie
directions: Place lemonade in a large mixing bowl and beat about 30 seconds.
Gradually spoon in ice cream and blend.
Fold in whipped topping, whipping until smooth.
Spoon mixture into pie crust. Freeze until firm, 4 hours.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place onion in crock-pot.
Add chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook on low for 7 to 9 hours; high for 3 to 4 hours.
Good served over hot buttered spaghetti. May also be cooked in the oven.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini and onion; add salt.
Let stand overnight; drain, rinse in cold water; drain.
Combine vinegar, nutmeg, peppers, sugar, dry mustard, cornstarch and turmeric.
Bring to a boil; add zucchini and cook for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Ladle in hot jars and seal.
Place in canner, cover jars with hot water. Boil for 10 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn and put in grocery bag with soda.
In a pan, mix brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Put in bag with popped corn and shake.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute onion, garlic and pepper in butter.
Wash rice.
Combine with sauteed ingredients.
Add mushrooms that have been drained.
Add the broth.
Put in medium casserole dish and add the pecans.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 18 bean soup
directions: Cover mixed beans and salt with water and soak overnight. Drain.
Add 5 more cups water, meaty ham hock and ham and barley. Boil slowly 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, sliced onion, clove garlic and juice of lemon.
Simmer for 1 hour longer.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour the cranberries into the boiling water.
Cook until cranberries pop.
Let cool.
Mix together the jello, water, carrots, apples, pineapple and juice and nuts.
Stir all together and refrigerate. Stir a couple of times.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocado and mash with garlic powder, salt to taste and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice. Mix with onions and tomatoes.
Serve with taco chips or on salad of chopped lettuce with sour cream and salsa.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat eggs and Crisco oil together until foamy, then add and mix sugar, cinnamon and vanilla flavoring.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into long cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy ham glaze
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes. Brush frequently on ham during last 1/2 hour of baking.

title: green stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers and remove seeds.
Mix rice, raw hamburger, onion, garlic, paprika, egg, V-8 juice, salt and pepper together. Mix well.
Spoon into green peppers.
Place in large, greased roaster.
Mix 2 cups water and 2 cups V-8 juice together.
Pour over peppers.
Sprinkle bouillon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: pineapple molded salad
directions: Use juice from pineapple, add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups; bring to boil and add Jell-O and salt.
Remove from heat and add next 4 ingredients.
Pour into mold.

title: festive vegetables and dip
directions: Beat with electric mixer until well blended. Stir in 2 envelopes (1 box) McCormick collection spring vegetable.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Arrange fresh vegetable pieces into holiday shape.

title: hamburger jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set for 24 hours.
Form into 1/4-inch bars and put into dryer for 6 to 8 hours.

title: slovak style rabbit
directions: Remove rabbit from marinade, pat dry and cut into pieces. Sprinkle with salt and freshly ground pepper and brown in hot oil. Remove and set aside.
Add bacon to pan drippings; saute.
Add onion, carrot, garlic and parsley.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add flour, tomato paste, rosemary, bay leaf and return meat to saucepan.
Add stock and bring to a boil; add wine and simmer over low heat until tender.
Serves 2 generously.

title: orange pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Combine in saucepan sugar, eggs and pineapple.
Bring to a boil.
Add jello to hot mixture and cool.
Add lemon juice.
Whip evaporated milk until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells (could use graham cracker crust also).
Place in refrigerator until congealed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: classic green bean casserole(conventional or microwavable)
directions: In conventional oven:
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, put soup, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can French onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with rest of onions and bake
5 minutes longer.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt bouillon cubes in 6 cups boiling water.
Add onions and potatoes.
Simmer about 20 minutes, until fork-tender.
Add soup.
Bring to a boil.
Add frozen vegetables.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add cubed cheese, stirring until melted.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix ingredients together with electric mixer until well mixed (about 2 minutes).
Pour into well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Boil chicken and
pull from bones.
Cook noodles almost done. Add noodles and chicken soup in liquid that the chicken was cooked in.
Stir this
all
together
and let cook a short time.

title: mawmaw's crunchy potato chip salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine mayo and vinegar. Stir in cabbage, tuna, carrot, green pepper and onion. Cover and chill. Just before serving, add potato chips. Toss lightly.

title: coconut bon bons
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar, and coconut.
Chill 30 minutes. Shape into balls, chill again.
Then dip into melted chocolate chips.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Sprinkle garlic over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day add fresh tomatoes and mayonnaise.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients, except blueberries; blend.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix the crushed pineapple, sugar and pecans together and sit in refrigerator.
Dissolve jello in boiling water, stir in thawed strawberries.
Put in refrigerator until it begins to thicken. Fold in the pineapple, sugar and Cool Whip.
Tear angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Fold into the mixture.
Pour into punch bowl and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Blend shortening, sugar and eggs together at high speed.
Gradually add sweet milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake 8 or 9 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and place 1/2 large marshmallow in center of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Remove from sheet.
Cool and ice.
Makes 9 dozen cookies.

title: brownies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal apple muffins
directions: Beat egg; stir in all ingredients, mixing just to moisten. Pour into greased muffin pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Put bologna and sweet pickles through a fine grinder; then add horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, onion and salt.
Let stand for several hours or overnight.
Serve on crackers or small breads.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well and pour into lightly greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sylvia's apple torte
directions: Combine in processor the flour, 1/4 pound of butter, 1/3 cup sugar, white vinegar and 1/2 teaspoon water.
Press into pie or fluted edge pan.
Spread bread crumbs over top of dough.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and pat dry.
Prick each potato with a fork. Bake potatoes at 400° for one hour or until done.
Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out the pulp into a bowl.
Mash the potato pulp with hot milk until fluffy.
Beat in butter and green onions.
Add seasonings.
Fry the bacon until crisp.
Crumble and add to potato mixture.
Spoon potato mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Place potatoes on a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: darlene's lasagna
directions: Cook and stir turkey, onion and garlic in large saucepan until meat is brown and onion tender.
Add tomatoes and break up with fork.
Stir in tomato sauce, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat, simmer, uncovered, 1 hour, or until mixture resembles spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and oregano.
Reserve 1/2 cup meat sauce for thin top layer.

title: red raspberry punch
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in the hot water.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice and cold water.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: strawberry - banana ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick and creamy. Add bananas, lemon juice, vanilla, strawberries and Milnot. Pour into 1-gallon freezer and finish filling with milk. Freeze.

title: green rice
directions: Saute pepper, onions and celery; mix with other ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Tuna or chopped chicken may be added.
Serves 8.

title: evelyn simon's cheesecake
directions: Cream cottage cheese. Gradually add cream cheese and beat well. Beat in sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in lemon, vanilla, flour and cornstarch.
Add butter and mix until smooth.
Blend in sour cream. Bake in a greased 9-inch spring-form pan for 1 hour at 325°. Turn off oven and let cake stand at least 2 hours or overnight.
DO NOT OPEN OVEN FOR AT LEAST 3 HOURS.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a baking pan.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Add vanilla.
This will make a soft batter.
Put batter into baking pan and spoon fruit into the batter.
Bake about 45 minutes, in a moderate 350° oven or until batter is brown.

title: crisp apple cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle in crumbs; stir well.
Press on bottom of dish.

title: tiny cheesecakes
directions: Place graham cracker crumbs in lightly greased miniature muffin cups.
Shake to remove excess.
Cream 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into prepared muffin cups.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Top cooled cakes with mixture of sour cream, remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Bake for 5 minutes longer. Garnish with red or green cherries.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: pie cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and keep frozen until ready to serve. Cut into squares and serve on crisp lettuce.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Beat egg yolks until stiff; add sugar, salt, lemon and cream. Stir together in double boiler until thick.
(Don't worry if curdles.)
Cool.
Beat remaining pint of whipped cream.
Add to salad.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until it becomes light lemon in color. Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add flavor and salt; mix well.
Sift flour one time.
Empty can of milk into measuring cup and add water to make one cup.
Add flour and milk alternately. Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Start in cold oven.
Time could vary depending on oven.

title: spinach spread
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve in scooped out pumpernickel roll. Garnish with greenery of season.
Serve with crackers or party bread.

title: fluffy pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat condensed milk whipped topping and lemon juice with an electric mixer for 2 minutes on medium speed. Stir in crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.
Pour mixture into prepared pie crust.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: chocolate no-cook bonbons
