directions: Melt butter. Add coconut, powdered sugar, pecans and milk. Mix well and roll into small balls (approximately 3/4 inch in diameter).
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in the top of a double boiler.
Dip each bonbon in the chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Sift flour, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Gradually add to butter mixture.
Pat the dough into a well greased oblong pan.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to beaten egg white and brush on top of dough.
Add pecans and press in.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool slightly.
Cut into 1 x 2 inch sticks while still warm.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, vanilla and sugar well with hands.
Roll in 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper.

title: me-ma's meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: wild strawberry pie
directions: Place half of the strawberries in cooled baked pie shell.
With remaining strawberries, combine the sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and becomes clear.
Pour over the strawberries in the pie shell and chill. Serve cold with dollops of whipped cream.

title: party punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together for 5 minutes and cool.
In a blender, mix orange juice, lemon juice and bananas.
Combine with pineapple juice and sugar/water base.
Divide into 2 containers and store in freezer until ready to use.
Take out of freezer 1 1/2 to 2 hours before use.
To half the amount, add 1 large bottle ginger ale or 2 bottles if using entire amount.

title: mother's icebox cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Crush wafers, putting half on bottom of pan. Add filling.
Put remainder of wafers on top of liquid mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Lay graham crackers flat and cover entire cookie sheet. Sprinkle nuts over.
Boil butter and sugar for two minutes.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: cherry cha cha
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Fold marshmallows into Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 over cooled crust. Spread pie filling over mixture.
Add rest of cream mixture and sprinkle last 1/2 of crumbs over top.
Refrigerate.

title: anne's sausage dip
directions: *Or 1/2 pound Mexican Velveeta and 1 1/2 pounds regular Velveeta can be substituted.

title: nougat bars
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows over hot water, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Fold in Cheerios, nuts, coconut and salt.
Turn into buttered square pan (9 x 9-inch).
With hand protected by a piece of waxed paper, pat mixture evenly in pan. Spread chocolate in a thin layer over the top.
Chill until set, 1 hour.
Cut in 2 x 1-inch bars.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Mix
soda in buttermilk.
Then add crushed wafers and mix well.
Bake in oblong cake pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add chopped sirloin and onion; brown. Add bouillon cube and 1/2 cup water; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes on low heat.
Add cream of mushroom soup,
mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Take up and pour over egg noodles.

title: hawaiian rice salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Cut chunks in half. Combine rice, pineapple, coconut, almonds and cherries in a mixing bowl.
Blend sour cream, sugar, salt and reserved pineapple juice.
Pour over rice mixture.
Toss lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Prepare broccoli by cutting off stems and chopping tops in small pieces, use only tops for soup.
Cook broccoli, celery and onion in chicken broth until tender.
Melt butter in a separate saucepan, add flour with water and stir until thickened.
Add Velveeta, amount depends on personal preference.
Add milk and stir until cheese melts.
Add to pot with broccoli and broth. Heat carefully (don't boil) and season as desired, thicken as needed.

title: spicy zucchini soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or soup kettle, brown and crumble sausage; drain.
Add tomatoes, broth, zucchini, green peppers, celery, onion and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender. Add macaroni; heat through.
Yields 14 to 16 servings, 4 quarts.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in pie crust.
Mix water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Add strawberry Jell-O.
Mix and pour over strawberries.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: scrapple
directions: Cook ham in pressure cooker.
Take ham from bone.
Take scissors and cut ham in 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.
Keep 5 quarts broth on heat, in large pan.
Mix meal and flour together and add to broth until thick, very stiff and hard to stir.
Turn heat off and continue to stir.
Put in bread pans and cool.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Fry in oil until brown.
Serve with eggs or syrup.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an ovensafe bowl.
In another bowl, mix milk, flour and sugar together and pour over butter.
Pour peaches over mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: sweet-sour slaw
directions: Place shredded cabbage in covered dish in refrigerator for several hours.
Mix all ingredients, except cabbage, in order given (30 minutes before serving), pour over cabbage.
Mix and chill 30 minutes.
Minced onions may be added if desired.
(Cultured sour cream may be used instead of whipping cream.)

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350°, covered, for about 3 hours. Serve with noodles.

title: oven round steak
directions: Cut the steak in strips or pieces.
Place half in casserole. Top with layer of onions, green pepper (if desired), salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 can each of the soups over the steak.
Add another layer of meat, onions, green pepper and the balance of the soups.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: skillet chicken for two
directions: In nonstick frypan, place butter.
Melt over medium-high temperature.
Add chicken.
Cook, turning about 5 minutes or until brown on all sides.
Add onion and cook about 2 minutes more.
Add tomato, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes more or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Serve with florentine rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: baked red snapper
directions: Lay onion slices on greased flat casserole dish.
Place fillets on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour oil and wine over all.
Bake at 350° (preheated) in the oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until fish flakes easily.
Top with toasted almonds. Serves 3 to 4.
Serve lemon slices on side.

title: canned green tomatoes
directions: You will need pint jars.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: *A rolled rump, top round or bottom round roast can be used.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and refrigerate.

title: golden cauliflower soup
directions: In medium saucepan, cook cauliflower in 1 cup water until tender.
Reserve 1 cup cooked flowerets.
In blender or food processor, blend remaining cauliflower and liquid; set aside.
In large heavy saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender; stir in flour.
Gradually add remaining water, milk and bouillon; cook and stir until well blended and thickened.
Add cheese, pureed cauliflower, reserved flowerets and nutmeg; cook and stir until cheese melts and mixture is hot (do not boil).
Garnish with green onion.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place corn in 2-quart casserole.
Add sugar, flour and salt, mixing well.
Add eggs, milk and butter; stir.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yield 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender; keep broth.
Drain vegetables and mix with cans of soup and 1 1/2 soup cans of broth.
Mix together in bowl.
Chop chicken and line casserole dish.
Pour vegetable mixture over chicken.

title: kraut salad
directions: Stir sugar and vinegar together and bring to boil; allow to cool.
Drain and chop kraut well.
Mix oil, pepper, celery, dill seed, pimento and onion; toss and pour sugar-vinegar mixture over. Set overnight and drain.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease crock-pot with oil.
Add macaroni and other ingredients. Stir and cook on low for 3 hours and 15 minutes.
Add thin slices of cheese on top.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: In large
bowl, combine Velveeta and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Microwave 5 minutes.
Stir and add sausage.
Microwave an additional 3 to 5 minutes until dip is melted and well blended. Serve immediately with tortilla chips.

title: chicken breast yvonne
directions: Skin and halve the chicken breasts.
Flatten them slightly. Season both sides with salt and pepper.
Coat the chicken lightly with flour.
Heat the clarified butter in a large skillet; add the chicken (in 2 batches) and saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup of water and the cognac; season with salt and pepper.
Bring the mixture to a boil; cover and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Add peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and oats.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook potatoes (in chunks) until tender.
In small pan, melt 1/2 stick butter.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour, 1 1/2 cups water and 4 bouillon cubes.
Stir until thickened and cubes dissolve.
Mix all together in pot and simmer.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper; mix well until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well. Allow to sit in refrigerator for several hours before serving so flavors develop fully.

title: corn mexicala
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings until tender.
Add corn and olives; cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until thoroughly heated.
Spoon mixture into serving dish and sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: creamy eggless mayonnaise
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and mustard together.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add dry ingredients, water and vinegar and mix to a smooth paste.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and blend butter.
When ready to use, thin with cream or fold in whipped cream.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: amazing orange muffins
directions: Cut orange into 7 to 8 pieces and remove seeds.
Combine orange pieces and juice in blender.
Puree.
Add dates, egg and butter to blender, blend and then pour into mixing bowl.
Measure dry ingredients into separate bowl and mix well.
Pour dry ingredients into orange mixture and stir gently to combine.
Fill muffin tins (greased or filled with paper liners) and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: yummy beans
directions: Brown beef in skillet; pour off fat.
Put into Dutch oven. In skillet, saute bacon and onion until almost done.
Stir into Dutch oven and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on simmer 2 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Or place in large baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Mix milk, eggs and sugar mixture together.
Cook over medium heat until almost as thick as you want it to be.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Pour into cooked pie shell and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: eye of round pot roast(makes 4 servings)
directions: In heavy casserole with lid, brown roast in oil with garlic; add onion.
Pour in wine or broth.
Stir coffee powder into liquid.
Cover and roast at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat onto heated platter and keep warm.
Lift onions on top of meat and strain remaining juices.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer until juice are reduced to about 1/3 of the original volume, whisking all the time.
Add salt to taste.
Whisk in mustard, then margarine, one piece at a time.
Do not let sauce stand without whisking or it may separate.
Remove from heat; spoon sauce over meat.
Cut into 1/2 slices to serve.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Boil noodles.
When done, add cold water until cool.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese together.
Season mixture with salt and pepper. Brown onion and ground beef; drain.
Add tomato sauce and paste to beef.
Simmer mixture for 15 minutes.

title: betty's apple crisp
directions: Place apples in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Pour water and lemon juice over apples.
Mix sugar, flour, margarine and cinnamon together until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake cake and cut lengthwise.
Boil milk and flour until stiff, stirring constantly.
Cool; add sugar, salt, shortening, oleo and vanilla.
Add milk mixture and beat until fluffy.
Put filling between cake layers.
Cover cake and store in refrigerator one day.

title: easy artichoke dip
directions: Drain can of artichoke hearts and chop fine.
Combine artichokes with mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Season with lemon juice, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly and slightly browned.
Serve with your favorite cracker.
For a festive change, spread on party ryes and bake for an additional 10 minutes or so.

title: rhubarb-strawberry crisp
directions: Toss fruit with sugar and cornstarch and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients until crumbly.
Place fruit in a 9-inch casserole.
Smooth over and sprinkle topping evenly over fruit. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until topping is golden brown. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Mix 1/2 cup orange marmalade and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Spread in bottom of Bundt pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Melt margarine.
Dip biscuits, one at a time, in melted margarine, then roll in brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Stand biscuits in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate as soon as removed from oven.

title: biscotti (italian breakfast cookie)(makes 3 dozen biscuits)
directions: Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt in a separate bowl, then stir into butter mixture until thoroughly mixed.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.

title: creamed onions
directions: Slice enough onions in 1/4-inch slices to fill a medium size greased casserole.
Layer onion slices in casserole.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and dot generously with butter.
Pour heavy cream and light cream over top of onions but do not cover. Cover with generous layer of Italian bread crumbs.
(This can be made a day ahead, up to this point.)
Place casserole on baking sheet and bake in 300° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Onion-lovers will want seconds!

title: passover rolls *
directions: Combine meal, salt and sugar and set aside.
Bring water and oil to boil and add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Let mixture stand 15 minutes.
Shape into 8 to 12 balls.
With oiled hands, place on cookie sheet and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: seven (7) layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan.
Spread cracker crumbs.
Spread chocolate chips.
Spread butterscotch chips.
Spread coconut. Spread condensed milk.
Spread pecans.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potato and cook until soft.
Mash potato and add powdered sugar until it forms a dough.
Sprinkle wax paper with powdered sugar and roll out dough.
Spread with thin layer of peanut butter. Roll up and slice with sharp knife.
Keep refrigerated.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Peel, pit and
mash avocados in medium-sized bowl.
Add lemon juice, salt
and
pepper.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, salad dressing and taco seasoning mix.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add corn to beaten eggs.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix pineapple, orange sections, cottage cheese, orange Jell-O (dry) and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: new england shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet and drain.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with 2 cans creamed corn mixed together.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Top with eggs.
Spread eggs over entire top.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: cheese apples
directions: Place apples in 10-inch square baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, Cheddar cheese and salt in bowl.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add to apples; mix well.
Sprinkle with water and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May prepare apples and cover in salted water.
Drain apples and use as above omitting salt. May serve as side dish.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: pork chops with collard greens
directions: Wash and cut collard greens without stems.
Boil pork chops that have been trimmed of excess fat for 1 hour.
Add washed greens and boil for 30 minutes to 45 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.

title: broiled venison
directions: Combine 1 part vinegar or lemon juice with 3 parts salad oil or olive oil.
Season with spices and herbs.
Dill seed, celery seed, cloves, thyme, bay leaves, sliced onions, garlic cloves, celery leaves, parsley sprigs and sliced carrots are good.
Place the meat in a large bowl or pan and pour the marinade over it. Place in gas refrigerator 3 to 4 hours for small cuts, 10 to 12 hours for large cuts.
Drain and cook as desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring water to boil; add potatoes, onion, carrots and soup base. Cook until tender.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Beat spices with hammer; tie in cheesecloth bag.
Add spices and sugar to cider; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Remove spice bag; serve hot or cold.
Yields 20 servings.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in casserole dish at 350°.
Add croutons last 10 minutes of baking.

title: dumplings
directions: In large, deep bowl sift flour.
In small bowl beat egg.
Add egg mixture to flour, then enough water to make a soft dough. Beat dough mixture with a wooden spoon.
Cut small piece out of the dough with a tablespoon.
Working in batches, drop dough pieces into boiling water.
When cooked, dumplings will rise to top.
Drain cooked dumplings in a colander.
Rinse with water and transfer to separate bowl.
Gently toss with oil.
Makes about 50 (1-inch diameter) dumplings.
Serve with soup.

title: clemetine paddleford's crab imperial
directions: Melt butter; add flour and blend.
Add milk and seasonings; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour part of mixture into egg yolk, beating well.
Return to heat and cook until well thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add sherry, bread crumbs, crab, parsley and onion; mix gently.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with buttered crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 portions.

title: mushroom sauced pork
directions: Cut pork crosswise into 8 slices.
Wrap in plastic and pound to 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Spray skillet with Pam.
Add pork and cook on medium heat 4 minutes.
Turn and cook 2 to 4 minutes more until not pink.
Keep warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli for minimum amount of time on package.
Drain and put in greased casserole.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice and pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese slices.
Melt the margarine and stir in bread crumbs.
Pour over cheese slices and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fabulous turkey breast
directions: Combine orange juice concentrate, garlic, paprika, marmalade and tamari in a small bowl.
Cut 2 pieces of plastic wrap at least 18-inches long and overlap them about 2-inches, to create a very large piece of plastic wrap.
Place turkey in center of this sheet and cover turkey completely, on all sides, with orange mixture. Wrap turkey very tightly with wrap.
Use extra piece if you think it needs it.
(Repeat with foil.)

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans or use soup cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.)

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Over medium heat, mix together hamburger, taco seasoning, taco sauce, refried beans and jalapeno peppers.
Mix well.
Makes about 3 layers.
Heat until cheese melts, then eat with tortilla chips.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter generously two large cookie sheets.
In large pan, combine sugar, Karo and cook medium until drops like string from spoon.
Add peanuts.
Continue cooking until color of peanut brittle.
Add baking soda; stir well.
Mixture will boil up and bubble.
Pour onto prepared pans.
Spread out, getting peanuts into single layer.
Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: windsong pancakes
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Cook on griddle.

title: buttermilk bread(for bread machine)
directions: Bake on basic setting. Yield: 1 pound loaf.

title: wonderful banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar and add bananas and eggs.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture until just blended.
Do not overmix!
Makes 2 (5 x 9 x 3-inch) loaf pans (greased).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: low country shrimp boil
directions: Wash potatoes well.
Cut sausage into 2 or 3-inch pieces. Fill a 10-quart pot half full of water.
Put sausage, potatoes and seasoning in pot.
Cook until potatoes are almost done, about 15 minutes.
Add corn and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until shells turn pink.
Add salt if desired.
Drain and serve from pot.
Cook outside if possible.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: *Use fat-free dressing if watching fat content.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix jello, water, sugar, and lemon juice and let thicken while milk is chilling in the refrigerator. Whip milk and then mix with thickened jello mixture. Have pie plate covered with vanilla wafers for crust. Pour mixture over wafers. Keep in refrigerator.

title: potato cheese bake
directions: Remove skins from cooked potatoes.
Shred in bowl.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese, mix well. Turn into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with cornflakes, drizzle with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead and frozen until needed.

title: crow's nest
directions: Peel and slice apples as for a pie.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Cream butter and sugar.
Cook over low heat.
Add flour, hot water and nutmeg.
Stir until boiling.
Spoon over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are soft.

title: oven-fried parmesan chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk; stir well. Combine flour, Parmesan cheese, paprika and salt, stirring well. Dip each piece of chicken in egg mix and then in flour mix. Place in baking dish. Drip butter over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: delicious homemade rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening and stir to melt.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir to dissolve.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water (warm tap water should be sufficient).
When shortening mixture is cooled to lukewarm, add yeast, beaten eggs and flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and store in refrigerator 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mr. kim's chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Stir in beaten eggs, water and vanilla. Add all dry ingredients, oats and chips. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yield depends upon size of cookies.

title: 15 minute custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, hot milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust (uncooked).
Sprinkle nutmeg.
Bake in 475° oven for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, soups, water and milk in large 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and stir in the remaining ingredients.
Chill dough at least an hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam. Mix all ingredients and pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into 2 well-greased, floured cake pans.
Bake for about 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: First brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and cook.
Add 1 cup water and let simmer about 15 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until done.
Cook slow and stir or it may stick.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Cook fruit cocktail three minutes.
Add pineapple, Jell-O and cream cheese.
Stir until smooth, then partly chill.
Fold in whipped cream or Dream Whip, and chill until set.

title: easy chicken-cheese casserole
directions: Stew chicken in small amount of water, then bone it and cut it up.
Cook spaghetti in the chicken broth.
Saute green pepper with onion.
Save a little cheese for the top, then mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chop vegetables. Add 1 small bottle diet Italian dressing. Let marinate for a while. Add 1 package cooked spiral macaroni (Retina). Mix well.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, butter and milk, then coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tropical tea warmer
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags in slow cooker.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Stir in sugar, honey, orange juice, pineapple juice and orange slices.
Cover and heat on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve from pot.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Add water.
Combine sugars, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and flour.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
Spoon mixture evenly over apples.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey chili(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with fat-free cracked pepper crackers.
Contains 246 calories.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 1/3 tablespoons butter. Heat oven to 350°. Pour remaining 1/4 cup butter into 11 x 7 x 2 baking dish. Toss cooked spaghetti in butter. Cover spaghetti with 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce. Add in order listed:

1/2 pepperoni, 1/2 Mozzarella and all the onions and mushrooms. Sprinkle with Italian seasoning. Pour on top of this 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce. Top with remainder of Swiss cheese, pepperoni and lastly Mozzarella cheese. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven until bubbly. Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
In a large bowl, combine eggs and beat well; mix bread, milk, grated cheese and sausage.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Soak yeast in water in large bowl; add salt and sugar.
Mix in flour to form soft and smooth dough.
Do not let rise.
Cut into small pieces.
With floured hands, roll into ropes and twist into pretzel shape.
Place on cookie sheet covered with foil and dusted with flour.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 3 to 6 dozen.

title: japanese fruit cake pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 50 or 55 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 12 ounces of chocolate chips.
Spread on mixture.
Cool.

title: lemon chess cake bars
directions: With pastry cutter, cut ingredients together until in small pieces (as in pie crust).
Press into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Mix sugar, jello and cornstarch.
Add water and cook slowly until thick.
Slice strawberries in crust.
Pour cooled mixture over.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: caramel icing
directions: Place butter and brown sugar in a heavy pot and heat 2 minutes. Add 1/3 cup milk and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
If too stiff to spread, a small amount of milk may be added.
Ices 2 layers.
Double recipe for 3 to 4 layers.

title: easy hamburg casserole
directions: Put hamburg in bottom of 2-quart casserole; layer the potatoes on top of hamburg.
Add carrots, onions and chopped peppers.
Put the tomatoes and seasonings in next.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape mixture into a loaf in a 9-inch square pan.
If desired, spread additional 1/4 cup catsup on loaf. Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until well browned.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crushed chips.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle crushed chips over top.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Makes a large casserole.
Can be frozen.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble; drain.
Stir-fry onion in bacon drippings for 2 minutes.
Add rice and stir-fry 7 to 8 minutes.
Add soy sauce, water and bacon.
Reduce heat.
Pour eggs on top of rice; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until eggs are cooked.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
To this, add egg and sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Mold into balls (walnut size) and press lightly on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs. Add 1 quart buttermilk. Dissolve whole bran in boiling water; add along with Bran Buds to sugar mixture.
Stir in flour, salt and soda.
Pour into greased muffin tin cups. Bake at 400° for 16 to 19 minutes.
Batter will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar, eggs and flavorings. Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open oven door for 1 hour.

title: peppery chicken wings
directions: Preheat broiler.
Separate chicken wings; remove and discard tips.
In medium bowl, combine oil and cayenne pepper.
Add wings, turning until well coated.
Place wings on broiler pan and broil about 8 inches from heat, turning occasionally for about 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake vigorously.

title: my best chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots in margarine 10 minutes. Add flour; stir well. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: tex-mex chicken(low-fat - low calorie)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken pieces, skinned side up, in a 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
Place onion slices on chicken.
Pour salsa over chicken.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with onion; drain and season to taste.
Spread meat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Combine 2 cans of soup and 2/3 cup of water.
Blend well.
Pour over cheese.
Place frozen Tater Tots decoratively over top of soup.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
In blender or mixer, blend milk and marshmallow cream.
Add cream cheese.
Cut up any fruit and dip!
Wonderful!

title: dirty rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° in a Bundt pan for 55 to 60 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: pepperidge farm party sandwiches
directions: Mix mustard, Worcestershire
sauce,
onion,
poppy seed and butter together.
Split
rolls
(I	use
electric
knife). Coat both sides of rolls
with
mustard spread.	Add one piece of ham and one piece of
Swiss cheese.
Put back in foil tray. Cover with tinfoil and heat at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grandma jacobs' prune bread
directions: Mix the flour, soda, nutmeg, allspice, salt and sugar.
In separate bowl, mix oil, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients; mix just until all ingredients are moist.
Cook prunes just enough to soften them, then chop.
Fold in prunes and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pumpkin patch pie
directions: Place sherbet in bowl; stir until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of the Cool Whip until well blended.
Spoon into crust.
Sprinkle with chopped Oreo cookies, pressing firmly into sherbet.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with finely chopped Oreo cookies and candy pumpkins, if desired.
Store leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in a 400° oven for 35 minutes.

title: hot toddy
directions: Dissolve sugar with 2 tbsp. hot water.
Add rest of ingredients and add hot water to taste.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until brown.
Add chopped ingredients and fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add rice.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally. Mix eggs and soy sauce in bowl.
Pour over rice and stir until cooked.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Soft, fat free or off brand cream cheese will not work.
Mix cream cheese, parmesan and green onions until well mixed.
Wash and dry mushroom caps. Mound filling in mushroom caps.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese mixture is browned on top.
To stuff approximately 60 mushroom caps, use 3 8 oz. cream cheese, 2 cups parmesan cheese, and 2 bunches of green onion, tops only.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except buns.
Butter buns, put mix inside each bun.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: frosty orange punch
directions: Combine sugar, salt and water.
Stir until sugar dissolves; add orange and lemon juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Also add ice.
Can add 1 pint sherbet just before serving.

title: lucy's special casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Reserve 1/4 cup of fat.
Cook celery, green pepper and onions in reserved fat.
(Do not overcook!)
Put sausage, vegetables and almonds into a 3-quart baking dish.
Add rice and broth; mix well.
Bake at 350° until liquid is completely absorbed (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
If you like your rice softer, you might add more chicken broth and cook a little longer.
Delicious with congealed salad and green vegetables.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange the chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with the Swiss cheese.
Combine the soup and wine and spread on the chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle with the stuffing, then drizzle the butter over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: savannah red rice
directions: Fry the bacon or ham in a heavy saucepan. Add tomato paste and all other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender. When everything is mixed, put bacon slices on top.
Cook in oven until mixture is dry.
Should take about 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown beef and onions in 2 to 3 tablespoons hot fat.
Add beans and soup and cook gently for 10 minutes.
Make a paste from chili powder, flour, water and salt and blend into beans.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for approximately 45 minutes. Serve with hot corn bread.

title: squash or pumpkin soup
directions: Saut onion in butter.
Add mashed squash or pumpkin and mix well.
Slowly add broth and half and half, stirring constantly. Season to taste and bring to boiling point, stirring constantly. Serve in hollowed and baked small pumpkins or squash.
Sprinkle toasted pumpkin seeds on pumpkin soup just before serving.

title: microwave potato salad topping
directions: In 1-quart casserole place 1 tablespoon olive oil and chopped green onions, including some of green top.
Microwave on High 1 to 3 minutes, until bright green.
Stir in 1/2 cup olive oil, cider vinegar, chopped dill pickle, dill weed, salt and pepper.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and celery.
Cook macaroni almost done, then drain.
Mix well with all ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: easy pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in
water;
add salt, shortening and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat until
smooth;
add remaining flour, roll out and place on a 14
x 7-inch greased baking sheet.
Spread with tomato sauce.
Brown beef
with
the onion, oregano, thyme and garlic salt.
Drain and
spread
over sauce.
Top with cheese. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: taco wheels(appetizer)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl. Spread on tortillas. Roll as for jelly roll. Slice as desired. Arrange on serving plate. Serve with salsa.

title: breakfast eggs
directions: Spread oleo in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Shred cheese.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour in pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown chops in slightly greased skillet; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir potatoes, 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 can of onions with soup mixture; mix all together.
Spoon mixture into a 4 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chops over mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake 5 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: chicken breast in lemon sauce
directions: Saute chicken in butter until done through center.
Remove chicken to broiler proof platter.
Pour wine into frying pan.
Add lemon peel and juice.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper to chicken.
Turn down heat.
Add slowly, cream to wine lemon mixture; stir constantly.
Pour sauce over chicken.
In separate pan, fry mushrooms (fresh) in butter.
Add to chicken. Dot each breast with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Place under broiler for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with wild rice.

title: banana whip
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water in blender.
Blend until dissolved, about 30 seconds.
Add milk and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir in blender until partially melted.
Add banana slices; blend until smooth.
Makes 2 3/4 cups or 5 servings; 45 calories per serving.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal pancakes
directions: You start the batter for these cake-like pancakes the night before.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the first 5 ingredients until the mixture is moist.
Fold in zucchini.
Heat butter in a skillet over medium heat.
Use 2 tablespoons of mixture for each round. Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until brown.
Makes 12 rounds or 6 servings.

title: cheese and mushroom manicotti or shells
directions: Combine half of the Mozzarella with the Cheddar cheese, mushrooms, olives, onion, celery, crumbs, egg, milk and parsley. Mix spaghetti sauce and water; pour half of the mixture into a baking dish.
Stuff manicotti with the cheese mixture, placing stuffed shells on the sauce.
Add remaining sauce and sprinkle with small
amount of Parmesan, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove foil; sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and bake 10 more minutes.

title: traditional chex party mix
directions: Melt margarine in open roasting pan in preheated 250° oven. Stir in seasoning.
Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels, stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: ring-a-lings
directions: Sift flour and salt onto waxed paper or foil.
Cream butter with sugar until well blended in a medium sized bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients, blending well to make a soft dough.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Chill several hours (overnight preferably) until firm enough to handle.
Roll dough, a teaspoon at a time, into marble size balls between palms of hands.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make a hollow in the center of each with thumb.
Fill with about 1/2 teaspoon jam.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until delicately golden.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: grated potato casserole
directions: Wash the potatoes. Cover with water and cook with skins on. Cook until potatoes are half done.
Pour off water and let cool. Skin potatoes and shred them.
Put in a casserole dish.
In a pan, heat on the stove the cheese, whipping cream, milk, dry mustard and salt until the cheese is melted.
Pour the sauce over the potatoes and stir in.
Sprinkle the top with paprika.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
The first half hour, keep it covered with foil and the last half hour take the foil off.
Can prepare this the day before and have refrigerated 24 hours and then bake.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and confectioners sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time until blended.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Mix about 3 minutes until well blended. Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 45 minutes until done.
Grease and flour pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat undiluted soup.
Mix gelatin with 3 tablespoons water. Mix with soup. Gradually mix with cream cheese. Add remaining ingredients. Chill in serving dish or mold. Serve with crackers.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add spices and stir.
Then add tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Let simmer for 2 to 3 hours or longer.

title: sweet potato pie(9-inch)
directions: Add the eggs to the sweet potatoes and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450°.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well. Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool on sheet 1 minute.
Then remove to wire rack. Yields about 6 to 6 1/2 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender in salt water.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients except crackers into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Crush crackers over top and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add chocolate syrup, then flour.
Bake at 350° in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Blend 1/2 cup butter, 2 tablespoons creme de menthe and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Mix until spreadable and spread over brownies.
Melt in double boiler 6 ounces chocolate chips and 6 tablespoons butter.
Let cool and spread over mint layer.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan on 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and eggs together.
Pour melted margarine over mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: 5-part salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add sherbet; stir until it melts.
Add 11 ounces of oranges.
Pour into 1-quart mold when jello starts to thicken.
Chill until set.
Mix oranges, pineapple, coconut, marshmallows and sour cream.
Just before serving, put fillings in the center and around the sides of the jello mold.

title: bean soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Saute onions and bell pepper, add beans with juice.
Add everything else but milk and cheese. Simmer a little while, taste and add more ingredients according to cravings.
Add milk and Parmesan cheese last (extra sharp Cheddar is great, too).
Return to boil.
Cover.
Turn off.
Leave it alone.
Reheat later, when ready to serve and serve with cornbread.
Makes 10 servings.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini; drain and rinse with cold water.
Cut salami in strips.
Quarter and seed red pepper; cut into thin strips.
In large bowl, mix vinegar, basil, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic. Using a whisk, beat in oil until well blended.
Lightly mix tortellini, parsley, salami, pepper and cheese. Cover; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat salted water (1/2 teaspoon to 1 cup water) to boiling. Add broccoli (cover and heat to boiling and cook until tender, 10 to 12 minutes).
Drain and place in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk with hand beater until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese. Mix Bisquick and margarine until crumbly and sprinkle over cheese. Bake until light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to firm ball stage (240°).
Wipe away crystals from pouring side of pan and allow to cool, undisturbed, for about 5 minutes.
Beat egg whites.
Add syrup very slowly, beating constantly.
Add remaining syrup more rapidly.
Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture holds it shape and becomes slightly dull.
Stir in nuts.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Cook in a heavy pan.

title: cool crumby pie
directions: With mixer, blend cream cheese for 1 minute.
Add sugars to chocolate.
Blend with milk to silky texture.
Scoop in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread out over crust and cool for 30 to 40 minutes. Prepare topping by mixing the remaining ingredients in a bowl. Spread over pie and refrigerate to set.

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Jell-O pudding, eggs, water, almond extract and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Blend.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of batter in separate bowl.
Stir in 1/4 cup of chocolate.
Spoon batter alternately into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pecan chew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Cook for 20 minutes or until done.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and rind and mix until well blended.
Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cream cheese mixture; chill.
Layer fruit in 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Top with creamy mixture.
Garnish with chopped nuts if desired.
Chill until serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute celery and onion in a small amount of margarine until soft.
Stir in soup and Velveeta and cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in cooked chicken.
In large pan combine spaghetti and sauce.
Add enough broth to keep mixture very moist.
Transfer to 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° until hot.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, egg, peanut butter, water and vanilla.
To this mixture, add the flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
When chilled, add last ingredients with rice.
Add whipped cream.

title: okra and tomatoes(no-fat, no sugar)
directions: Saute okra and onion together; add tomatoes.
If using fresh tomatoes, add 1/4 cup of tomato sauce.
Cook for about 15 minutes. Serve over rice or toss with thin spaghetti or capellini.

title: imperial chicken
directions: After removing crusts, allow bread to dry; crush bread crumbs. Mix crumbs with cheese, chopped parsley, salt and pepper.
Dip each piece of chicken in melted oleo, then in crumb mixture. Arrange pieces in flat pan, lined with foil and oiling the foil. Dot each piece of chicken with 3 small dots of oleo.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes. Do not cover.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Place bread cubes in a large, low microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cubes begin to dry.
Sprinkle with flavored salt and toss with melted butter to coat evenly.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring each minute until crisp and dry.

title: persimmon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, pour into unbaked, 9 inch pastry shell. Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix together sugar, oleo and juice.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Add crushed wafers and nuts; form into small balls.
Roll balls in coconut.
Makes 100 balls.

title: cheese balls
directions: In microwave, heat cheese until it is soft.
Mix all three ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet (350°) until golden brown.
Good served warm.
May be reheated in microwave when ready to serve.
Freezes well.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and oleo well.
Add sugar and 3 eggs.
Mix well.
Alternate 3 cups of flour and 3 eggs.
Place in cold oven and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Makes 3 loaf pans.

title: aunt lana's cheesecake
directions: Cream the cream cheese with mixer.
When fluffy, add sugar, a little at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown meat. Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Add all other ingredients to meat.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Slice the lemons as thin as paper, rind and all, no seeds. Combine them with the sugar and mix well.
Let stand 2 hours or longer, preferably, blending occasionally.
Add the beaten eggs to the lemon mixture and mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli, celery and onion in butter.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz until bubbly.
Add rice.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: six layer casserole
directions: Lightly brown sausage or beef; drain on paper towel and cut into
small
pieces.
Into
a 2-quart buttered casserole, place vegetables
in
order given (potatoes, onions, carrots, rice
and crushed
tomatoes).
Sprinkle
with
the
seasonings mixed together and top with sausage or beef and cover.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: white batter bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle yeast into water; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture.
Stir in flour; batter will be fairly stiff.
Beat until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until more than doubled in bulk, about 40 minutes.
Stir batter down.
Beat vigorously, about 1/2 minute. Turn into one greased 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot pickled peppers
directions: Cut bell peppers into thin strips and pack into pint jars. In each jar, add one red pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 teaspoon dill seed.
Combine salt, vinegar and water. Bring to a boil and pour over peppers.
Seal.
Let stand a few weeks before serving.

title: happiness cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Flavor with love and kindly service.
Fold in prayers, faith and enthusiasm.
Spread all into your daily life.
Blend well with human kindness.
Serve with a constant smile and it will satisfy the hunger of many people less fortunate then ourselves.

title: single pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in Crisco until crumbly.
Add 2 tablespoons water, one at a time, toss with fork.
Add milk and vinegar, toss with fork.
Form into ball and refrigerate to chill. Roll on cloth.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Spray sheet cake pan with PAM.
Place pecans and coconut in pan.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Mix margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Spoon over batter and cut, swirl into spread.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Add sour cream.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry rice in shortening until light brown; add water and 1 tsp. salt and boil until soft; drain. Saute onion in a little fat. Add hamburger and fry until crumbly. Mix with tomatoes and peppers. Add rice and all other ingredients. Put in greased casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of a 9 inch pie plate.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together and spread over beans. Layer guacamole, cheddar cheese, tomatoes, olives, and onions. Serve with chips.

title: oriental salad
directions: Stir flour and sugar together.
Add to juice.
Add beaten eggs.
Cook in double boiler until thick and glossy.
Cool.
Mix pineapple and pears into cooked mixture.
Pour into pan.
Cover with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, then coconut and nuts.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients; form into a ball.
Mix the last 3 ingredients together; roll cheese ball in mixture.

title: potato gratin
directions: Rub a shallow 3-quart baking dish with cut sides of garlic halves; discard garlic.
Coat dish with cooking spray.

title: no cook hunters peanut butter balls
directions: Nothing else added.
Simply mix well, shape into 1 inch balls. Excellent for hikers, snacks, etc.

title: potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake potatoes.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out potato, leaving 1/4-inch potato in shell.
Deep fry potato skins in fat that has been preheated to 350° and fry until lightly crisp.
Remove from fat; drain.
Add 1/2 slice Cheddar cheese to each potato half and sprinkle bacon bits over each.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.
Serve hot with sour cream and chives.

title: mashed potato delight
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and almonds.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Drizzle with butter and sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl, combine all crust ingredients, except marshmallows, until crumb mixture forms.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Immediately sprinkle marshmallows on top and bake 1 to 2 minutes longer or until marshmallows begin to puff.
Cool while preparing your topping.

title: irish baked potato
directions: Bake potatoes for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: harvard carrots
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add carrots and let stand over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add butter and serve.

title: speedy bean 'n' bacon joes
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add beef and brown, stirring to break up meat; drain fat.
Add soup, water and catsup.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add more water if desired.
Serve on buns.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Put all together, toss with fork.
Fill mushroom caps and bake in 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until melted.

title: cabbage with caraway
directions: Slice cabbage into wedges 1 1/2-inches thick.
Melt margarine in large skillet; add in cabbage, sugar, parsley, pepper and bouillon stock.
Cover and cook for 12 minutes, basting with pan juices several times.
One minute before done, sprinkle with caraway seed. Remove cabbage to serving dish.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: italian gnocchi(potato dumplings, little ears)
directions: To mashed potatoes, add milk and margarine.
Sift flour and add to the potatoes.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and shape into little balls with your fingers.
(They will look like little ears.)
Boil water and drop gnocchi in.
Boil 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with Italian sauce or with a meat dish.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine, then add all ingredients. Stir well and place in hot oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.
Remove from oven.
Lightly brush with margarine and slice.

title: wine and lemon chicken
directions: Marinate chicken, wine, onion slices and lemon for 4 to 6 hours.
Place chicken, wine, lemon and onion in a baking pan. Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until cooked (approximately 1 hour).
Serve with excess marinade sauce.

title: noodle ring with meatballs
directions: Combine onion, eggs, bread crumbs and hamburger meat. Add salt and pepper to taste. Mix and roll into small meatballs.

Roll each meatball in flour and brown in a large skillet with 1/4 cup oil. When meatballs are brown, add 2 cans of vegetable beef soup and 1/2 can of water. Simmer on low for 30 minutes. When meatballs are done, add the condensed milk to the mixture and simmer on low until the gravy is thick. (If needed, a flour and water mixture may be added to thicken.) Cook
wide egg noodles according to package directions. Place the noodles on a large plate and pour the meatballs and gravy over the noodles.

title: temptation cake
directions: Bake cake mix in large oblong pan using milk instead of water. Punch lots of holes in cake top with a toothpick when done. Bring to boil the sugar and crushed pineapple.
While mixture is hot, pour over the cake, then cool to room temperature.
Blend together the cream cheese and pudding mix with milk.
Pour over cooled cake and chill until mixture thickens.
Cover cake with sliced bananas and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and coconut.
Add cherries on top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar.
Follow pudding directions by adding 2 cups milk.
Spread 3/4 of peanut butter mixture in pie crust.
Spread pudding on top of peanut butter mixture.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture on top of Cool Whip.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Butter 9-inch glass dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Double recipe for 9 x 13 pan.

title: broccoli topped baked potatoes
directions: Wash, dry and rub potatoes with vegetable oil.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 60 minutes.
When potatoes are close to done, cook broccoli in water until still slightly crunchy.
Do not drain. Mix in sour cream and cheese and heat thoroughly, but do not boil. Cut potatoes in half (lengthwise) without cutting all the way through.
Open potatoes and fluff inside with a fork.
Spoon broccoli mixture over each potato and serve immediately.

title: beth's ham ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.

title: shrimp cantonese with rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute shrimp in butter until pink.
Add celery and onions; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add spinach and vegetables (drained).
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Blend pepper, soy sauce and cornstarch; stir into shrimp -vegetable mixture. Cook and stir until sauce is clear and thickened, about 2 minutes. Serve with or over rice.

title: hot dirty rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; set aside.
Combine water, wings and gizzards in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add livers and cook until tender.
Drain, reserving 3/4 cup liquid.
Remove meat from wings.
Coarsely chop wing meat, gizzards and livers.
Set aside. Brown sausage in Dutch oven, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain and set aside.

title: shredded potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Boil potatoes in their skins until tender, but firm.
Chill, peel and grate potatoes.

title: victoria sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch sandwich tins.
In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar together until pale and fluffy.
Gradually add the eggs and warm water and mix well.
Sift in the flour and beat thoroughly until well blended.

title: santa fe casserole
directions: In medium skillet brown ground beef, stirring until cooked through; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning; blend well.
In small bowl combine broth and flour.
Add to meat mixture; bring to a boil to slightly thicken.
Stir in sour cream and green chilies.
In lightly greased 13 x9-inch baking dish, layer half of chips, half of beef mixture, half of cheese and half of onions.
Layer again with remaining ingredients, ending with onions.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: howard's spread
directions: Mix together with a fork until smooth and well mixed.
Serve with crackers.

title: ham and cheese bake(serves 8)
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except the potatoes in a large bowl and stir to mix well.
Set aside.
Coat a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Slice the potatoes 1/4-inch thick and line the bottom and the sides of the pan with the slices to form a crust.
Pour the egg mixture over the potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour until the filling is set and the top is touched with brown.
Allow to sit for 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into squares and serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, beating well after each egg. Sift dry ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Add food coloring to cake mixture.
Alternately add buttermilk and flour mixture, starting with milk and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and vinegar and beat.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft.
Beat peanut butter and sugar. Slowly add milk, beating until well blended.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze before serving.

title: grandma's catsup
directions: Boil until thick, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking (about 2 hours).
Pour into bottles and seal.

title: cry baby cookies to make with kids on a rainy day
directions: Mix all together and drop by the tablespoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake about 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Shape mixture into a log.
Roll in chili powder.

title: chilighetti
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and drain.
Add Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Put a layer in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Next layer 1/2 the chili beans.
Next, layer 1/2 of uncooked spaghetti.
Repeat layers, then pour can of tomato juice over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to rolling boil. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat, about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at one time; continue beating until smooth.
Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls 3-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Cool away from draft. Cut off tops.
Pull out any filaments of soft dough.
Carefully fill puffs with vanilla cream pudding.
Replace tops, dust with confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: chocolate cookie pudding
directions: Crush cookies and place on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1 cup of crumbs.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk and blend well.
Add 1/2 of whipped topping to the cream cheese mixture.
Spread over crackers and mix pudding according to package directions.
Place on top of cream mixture, then spread remaining whipped topping on top of pudding.
Sprinkle top with remaining cookies.

title: cordon bleu casserole("quick and easy")
directions: Rinse broccoli under water to thaw and separate; pat dry. Line bottom of 8 x 8-inch casserole dish with bread.
Top with chipped chicken, chipped ham and broccoli.
Stir onion powder into soup and pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Can be covered and chilled overnight and baked the next day, if desired, or baked immediately in conventional oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: mexican bean casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and drain.
Mix in beans, tomatoes and soup.
Pour into greased casserole dish; put crushed chips and end with grated cheese on top.
Bake at 400 degrees till cheese is melted.

title: baked grated carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add carrots, cinnamon, nutmeg and juice to an ovenproof casserole dish and mix well.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes or until tender.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Put in 9 x 12-inch baking dish in order listed. Put corn flakes in melted butter and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Add all other ingredients and mix well, until consistency of formed dough.
Put dough in refrigerator at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: corn flake christmas wreath cookies(holiday)
directions: Melt butter over medium heat. Stir in marshmallows until melted. Add green food coloring. Turn off heat and add corn flakes. Fold into mixture with a spoon. Run hands under cold water and form wreaths on wax paper. Place red hots on top to look like berries and let stand until firm.

title: honey ham glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet and bring to a simmer; turn off heat.
(Enough for 1 1/2 pound ham.)

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sugar, brown sugar and mix. Stir in chocolate chips. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Place cream cheese mixture on a large piece of plastic wrap, shape into a ball. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Just before serving, roll cheese ball in pecans. Serve with graham crackers.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter.
Add ground beef.
Cook until browned.
Drain.
In a saucepan, add ketchup, tomato paste, water, mustard, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, relish and sugar.
Pour this over ground beef mixture.
Add salt and pepper. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: opera fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar, corn syrup and salt in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook until a soft ball forms.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Set aside until lukewarm. Add flavoring.
Beat until thick and no longer glossy.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: baked round steak supreme
directions: Cut meat into serving portions, trimming fat; brown and set aside.
In bottom of Dutch oven, place potatoes.
On top of potatoes, spread Cheddar cheese soup, milk, 1/2 teaspoon Lawry's seasoned salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Lay meat portions on top of potatoes and spread mushroom soup on meat.
Place onion, bell pepper and mushrooms on top of soup and use the rest of the seasoned salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Place green beans on the very top.
Place in a preheated 350° oven and bake for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: a happy life
directions: In a pan of happiness, mix the above.
Add a pinch of tenderness and a tablespoon of truth.
Stir well in the sunshine. Roll out a loving crust.
Flow with contentment.
Keep all free from strife.
Fill with understanding and bake well as you life.

title: fish batter(english pub style)
directions: Mix together flour and salt.
Combine baking soda, vinegar and water.
Stir vinegar mixture and water into flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Dip fish into mixture allowing excess batter to drip back in bowl.
Fry in preheated oil until medium brown. Drain on paper towels.
This batter may be used on boneless chicken breasts and various vegetables.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend to moisten, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour about 3/4 of batter into well greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Add 3/4 cup chocolate-flavored syrup to remaining batter.
Mix well.
Pour over batter in pan.
Run knife through batter to marbleize.
Cook for 1 hour or until done.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners 10x sugar or cover with chocolate icing.

title: linus' blanket cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in large bowl and set aside.
Put oleo, cocoa and water in a pan and bring to boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: mini reubens
directions: Mix corned beef, sauerkraut and approximately 1/2 bottle of dressing. Line a cookie sheet with the cocktail rye bread. Add a tablespoonful of beef mixture to tops of bread. Top with a square of Swiss cheese. Bake at 325° until cheese is melted.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Stir in cheese while hot.
Spoon onto party rye bread slices.
Spread out.
Broil 5 minutes on bake in oven 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 35.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture; beat smooth with rotary beater.
In 8-inch skillet, heat cooking oil to 360°.
Release batter into hot oil, using a funnel, making a spiral shape.
Fry until golden, about 3 minutes.
Turn, using wide spatula and tongs.
Cook 1 minute more.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.
Makes 4 cakes.

title: crab-stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks with a fork.
Add crabmeat and next 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg whites.
Garnish with pimiento slices and fresh parsley sprigs.

title: chili(for a group)
directions: Brown ground beef. Put into large pot. Add other ingredients; cook for 2 hours at medium heat, until liquid is reduced. Beans, such as pinto or kidney, can be added if desired. Rubbed sage can be found in the spice aisle.

title: crockpot swiss steak
directions: In a shallow dish, combine flour, pepper and salt.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Add in flour mixture.
In a skillet, brown steak in butter or olive oil.
Transfer to slow cooker. Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the steak.
Cover and cook on low for
8 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Mix corn meal and cold water in saucepan.
Stir in boiling water and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Spoon into loaf pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Bake ingredients until smooth and easy to spread.
Spread mixture on flour tortillas and roll up jelly roll style.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Chill at least 3 hours, best if chilled overnight.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and unbeaten egg.
Add baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour into well buttered 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch for children
directions: Mix orange juice according to directions.
Mix with other juice.
Pour into punch bowl; add ice or ice ring mold.
Yields 50 servings

title: trifle
directions: Bake cake per directions in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut in cubes.
Layer ingredients.
Start with cake, pudding, Cool Whip and Skor.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle cake with liqueur, i.e., kahlua or other liqueur.

title: pineapple ice
directions: Mix the ingredients all together and put into a square container.
Put into the freezer.
When frozen, cut into squares and serve.
Very good.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred the cabbage using a sharp knife or a slicing blade of a food processor.
Put into a bowl with carrots and onions.
In a smaller bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Add to vegetables and mix well.
Let sit in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Add caraway seed before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken strata
directions: Lightly butter casserole dish. Place bread slices in bottom of casserole dish, then put cheese on top of bread.
Drain broccoli, place over cheese. Add chicken and arrange remaining bread over top.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, and mustard. Pour over bread. Garnish with pimento. Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 min.
Grate remaining cheese and sprinkle over top. Bake 5 min to melt cheese. Let stand for 10 min. before cutting.

title: tex mex soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and simmer. Cube Velveeta cheese and add after soup is warm. Allow cheese to melt, then add pasta and sour cream.

title: lillie's onion potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Chop onion.
Place potatoes in saucepan and cover with water.
Salt to taste.
Cook potatoes until tender.
Remove from heat and drain most of the liquid away. Slightly mash potatoes with a fork or masher.
(Do not mash until smooth.)
Add mayonnaise, onion and vinegar.
Mix all together and serve while hot.
Delicious with country style steak and gravy or any gravy.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach.
Tear leaves into pieces. Wash and dry watercress.
Remove stems.
Chill until crisp.
Combine spinach and watercress in a bowl. Combine garlic, salt, lemon rind, paprika, pepper and vinegar.
Add gradually the olive oil, stirring constantly, and beat in sour cream.
Pour dressing over greens and toss well. Crumble bacon over salad. Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan over medium heat.
Cook to a good boil.
Delicious on chicken or pork.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, cover and chill.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: sweet potato-applesauce bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut each sweet potato lengthwise in half. Place in an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and spread applesauce on potatoes.
Mix sugar, nuts and cinnamon and sprinkle over the applesauce.
Dot with butter and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: foolproof caramel icing
directions: Bring to rolling boil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Add powdered sugar until mixture is of spreading consistency.

title: hot taco dip
directions: A lasagna pan is good to use.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat broth, salt and white pepper to rolling boil in 2-quart saucepan over high heat.
Add dash of soy sauce.
(If broth is not heated to a rolling boil, egg will not form threads.)
Stir green onions into eggs.
Pour egg mixture slowly into broth, stirring constantly with fork until egg forms threads.
Serve in individual bowls and add a few pieces of chicken, if desired.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, cheese, celery, green pepper, onion, relish, pimiento and chopped eggs.

title: bean sprout salad
directions: Wash and drain bean sprouts; they must be dry.
Combine drained pineapple and water chestnuts with the bean sprouts; mix well.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Add cocoa and red food coloring.
Cook as directed.

title: spoon rolls
directions: In
a large mixing bowl, stir together yeast and sugar. Add
2 cups of flour and warm water.
Beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Add remaining flour, oleo and egg.
Beat again. Place
into
a
greased
bowl,
cover and refrigerate. When
ready to use, fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full and bake at
400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Extra batter will keep several days.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pudding cake
directions: Beat eggs well, add cream cheese and confectioners sugar. Pour over cake mix.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and butter to 240°.
Add raw peanuts. Cook to 290°.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda and remove from heat.
Pour mixture onto buttered marble slab or buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Steam the cabbage for 10 minutes.
Combine hamburger, stuffing, rice, egg, milk and salt.
Put heaping tablespoon of meat mixture in center of cabbage leaf.
Fold cabbage leaf like an envelope. Put in baking dish.
Pour tomato soup over cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Bring to boil water, cocoa and margarine, pour over flour mixture and stir well.
Add soda, vanilla, buttermilk, cinnamon and eggs. Pour into greased jelly roll pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Five minutes before cake is done, make frosting.

title: stir-fry squash
directions: Coat and heat oil in an electric wok or skillet.
Saute onion at 350° until limp, then add other vegetables.
Salt to taste and add Salad Supreme seasoning halfway through cooking.
Stir and cook until vegetables are crisp-tender or however you like them.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in very hot, low cholesterol oil. When browned, fill pot halfway with water (enough to cover 3/4 of the meat).
Turn stove to simmer.
Chop 2 onions into the gravy. Put Worcestershire sauce on meat.
Add all other ingredients to the water except gingersnaps.
Simmer (slightly rippling) for 3 hours.
Add gingersnaps, after removing meat, to thicken gravy. Serve with red cabbage and green beans.

title: turkey appetizers(good way to use leftover turkey)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle milk (1 tablespoon at a time) evenly over surface; stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in turkey, cheese and green pepper.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Finely chop graham crackers.
Combine graham crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into bottom and up sides of pan.
Combine Cool Whip, pudding mix and sour cream.
Pour half of the filling over the crust.
Slice bananas (kind of thin).
Layer bananas on top. Pour remaining filling over bananas.
Finely chop pecans and sprinkle over top.
Sets immediately, but can chill.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease quiche pan or pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Saute beef and onion; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix. Spread in plate; sprinkle with chiles.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake for 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife test comes out clean (8 to 10 minutes more).
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and lettuce.

title: lime frosted party punch
