directions: In punch bowl, combine chilled pineapple-grapefruit drink, lemon juice, cold water, soft drink powder and sugar.
Stir until soft drink powder and sugar are completely dissolved.
Top punch with large spoonfuls of lime sherbet.
Resting bottle on rim of the punch bowl, carefully pour in carbonated beverage.
Serve some sherbet with each cup of punch.
Serves 30 to 35.

title: zucchini hash browns
directions: In a medium bowl combine zucchini with salt. Let stand for 15 minutes and then squeeze out excess moisture with your hands. Stir in eggs, cheese and garlic. Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in a skillet over medium-high heat. Mound about 2 tablespoons of the zucchini mixture in the pan, flatten slightly to make a patty. Repeat until pan is filled, but don't crowd the patties in the pan. Cook the patties, turning once, until golden brown on both sides, about 6 minutes. Transfer the patties to a warm platter and repeat, adding more butter as needed.

title: zucchini bread(yields 6 servings)
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini in one bowl.
Mix flour, nuts, cinnamon, salt and baking soda in separate bowl.
Mix wet and dry ingredients alternately until well blended.
Grease and flour 2 to 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese and croutons over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies(old recipe)
directions: Combine the oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add the molasses and sour milk.
Sift
together
the flour, salt, cinnamon, ginger and baking
soda;
add	to
the
creamed mixture.
Put in the refrigerator
for
at
least
2 hours.
Roll; cut with cutter. Bake in
a 400° to 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until top of cookie springs back when touched.
Burns very easily.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour and measure, add soda, sift again.
Add flour and soda to mixture.
Add bananas, stir well and add nut meats.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with knife for doneness.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, salt, butter and sugars.
Then add vanilla and eggs and slowly add chocolate chips.
Then drop by teaspoons on baking sheet and bake until brown in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate zucchini cake(this is different and good.)
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, oil and sugar. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves; gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in zucchini. Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain beef and onion.
Add all other ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over tortilla chips.
Top with sour cream and grated cheese.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter or oleo in bottom of baking dish (9 x 13-inches). Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder together and spoon over butter.
Sweeten your fruit.
Add lemon juice and cinnamon.
Add flour or cornstarch with juice and pour over the batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mix bread
directions: Pour cooked grits into mixing bowl.
Add Crisco; let cool. Add part of the flour, salt, sugar and yeast.
Lastly, add warm water; beat with electric mixer for a few minutes, adding more flour while you beat by hand.
Turn out on floured board; work with hands until you have a workable dough.
Place in a large bowl; cover and let rise until double in size.
Punch down; place in pans and let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.

title: margie's nut bread
directions: Mix together egg, milk, vanilla and rolled nuts.
Add flour mixture to milk mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350° on greased bread pan.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water until only 3 tablespoons of water are left.
Mix shortening and sugar, then the eggs; beat until creamy. Stir in raisins and liquid plus vanilla.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg and beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Add chopped apples and nuts. Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan before cutting.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Bake in slow oven about 45 minutes at 300°.

title: new year's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients into dough.
Roll out, using small amount of flour to keep from sticking.
Cut with floured cookie cutters. Decorate with sugars and/or candies if desired.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini parmesan *
directions: Dip a slice of zucchini in egg, then bread crumbs.
Continue until all the zucchini is breaded.
Heat oil in a large frying pan and fry the zucchini until golden brown.
Remove from oil and drain on paper towels.
In a baking dish, layer with spaghetti sauce, zucchini, onion and cheeses.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef and onions. Separately cook rice according to package directions. Add other ingredients and simmer while rice is cooking (25 to 30 minutes). Rice and meat mixture can be mixed together or served separately.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash 2 cups bean mix; place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans;
let soak overnight.
Drain beans; add next 5 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Yield:
8 cups soup.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Add all ingredients except oatmeal and peanut butter.
Bring to a boil; cook for 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter.
Then add oatmeal.
Spread on greased paper or drop from spoon.

title: bread pudding
directions: Boil milk.
Keep mixing and add all the ingredients.
Mix except the cinnamon and 2 tablespoons of sugar which you sprinkle on top of pudding.
Pour into greased (butter) deep dish and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with whipped or plain cream or milk.

title: bagel croutons
directions: Note:
Experiment with various bagel types; pumpernickel is really good.

title: jello cake
directions: Take any white or yellow cake mix and bake as usual.
While cake is still hot, make holes with a wooden spoon end all over cake.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar, cranberries and apples together and let stand for awhile, then add remaining ingredients and serve.

title: 9 cup cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, according to package.
Mix lemon juice and oil. Combine with drained macaroni.
Chill several hours, stirring occasionally.
Fold in shrimp, eggs, onion and celery.

title: cheddar pennies
directions: Grate and work cheese and margarine together until creamy. With your hands, mix flour, salt and cayenne until smooth.
Chill dough for an hour, then roll to 1/2-inch thick on floured board and cut in rounds.
Place in preheated 350° oven and bake 15 minutes or until pale gold.
Good with soup and salad.

title: baked egg casserole(may mix up night before.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together gently.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Place scraps of bread (leftovers from donut shapes) in the bottom of a 13 x 9 pan. Then layer cheese, broccoli and ham. Mix together the last 5 ingredients and soak each piece of bread in mixture before laying them on top. Pour remaining mixture over the top. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut pecan cake
directions: In a mixing bowl combine eggs, 2 cups of the sugar, oil, and 2 teaspoons coconut extract.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl combine flour, baking powder, and salt; add to egg mixture alternately with buttermilk, just until moistened.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Spoon into a greased 10-inch bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60-70 minutes, or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: chocolate peanut butter sundaes
directions: Blend peanut butter and chocolate syrup.
Divide ice cream among 4 dessert dishes.
Spoon sauce over ice cream.

title: mint jelly
directions: Wash mint leaves and stems and put in a large saucepan; crush with a masher or drinking glass.
Add the water and bring quickly to a boil.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 10 minutes. Strain and measure 1 2/3 cups into large saucepan.
Add lemon juice and a few drops of food coloring.
Stir in sugar; put over high heat and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
At once, stir in pectin, then bring to a full rolling boil and boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skim off foam with metal spoon and pour in hot sterilized jars.
Seal.
Makes about four 1/2 pint jars.

title: coke and cherry pie salad
directions: Bring cherries, water and sugar to boil in saucepan.
Add jello and food coloring, then let cool.
Add Coke, pineapple and nuts. Chill as you would jello.

title: banana bread #2
directions: Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°, then 45 to 50 minutes at 300°.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, persimmon pulp, and vegetable oil.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, and nuts.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch greased and flour bundt pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour or until done. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: tar-i-kal(norwegian lamb and cabbage dish)
directions: Cut the meat into serving pieces.
Cut the cabbage into chunks or thick slices.
Arrange meat and cabbage in a pan, sprinkling salt and pepper between (peppercorn can be placed in bag if desired).
Add water until it is about 2 inches over contents. Simmer on low heat until meat and cabbage is tender.
Serve on warm plates with boiled potatoes.

title: homemade cough medicine
directions: Warm honey; add glycerine and lemon juice.
If butter is used, it must be refrigerated.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: clam chowder
directions: Boil potatoes separately; use potato water (2 cups).
Saute onion and celery in salt pork drippings before adding to rest of ingredients.
May add 1 can tomato soup.
Simmer and serve. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in quart jar; shake well before using.
Half malt and half tarragon vinegar is good.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then add sugar and remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator.
This will keep 6 weeks.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix eggs and cottage cheese.
Add margarine, salt, onions and broccoli to muffin mix.
Bake in an approximate 9 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dinner salad
directions: Cook rotini as directed on package; drain and cool.
In a large bowl, combine lettuce, bell pepper and onion.
In a medium saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute, stirring continually.
Add pasta to lettuce, pour hot dressing over all.
Toss until well mixed.
Makes 12 servings. About 120 calories per serving.

title: california corn
directions: Mix corn, eggs, cornbread mix, garlic salt, green chilies and cooking oil together.
Mix well; pour half of corn into a greased 2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Add remaining corn and grated cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked custard, plain
directions: Scald milk; mix eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla. Beat well.
Slowly blend egg mixture into the hot milk in sauce pan.
Fill custard cups and place in water bath in large baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
After removing custard from oven, sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.

title: baked chicken and stuffing
directions: Prepare chicken, debone and remove skin.
Place in baking dish. Add 3 tablespoons margarine and sprinkle paprika, pepper and salt over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Prepare dressing according to directions on package.
Move chicken to one side of pan.
Add dressing and mound stuffing around chicken pieces.
Cover with foil and bake for at least 20 minutes longer.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion, drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15-20 minutes.
Top with grated cheddar cheese and serve with corn chips.

title: icebox lemon pie(as prepared by sollie buxton)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and enough butter or margarine to hold crumbs together.
Press crumb mixture into pie plate, forming a pie crust,
Bake 10 minutes or until browned.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Alternate flour, bananas and water, adding a little at a time; beat well. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured large loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Can substitute crab meat for the shrimp.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: oatmeal pecan pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell. Arrange whole pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until done in middle.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box; add pecans to cake mix.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake as directed on box. When cake is done, poke holes in the cake.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and caramel topping. Pour over cake making sure it goes into cake. Let cool completely, then top with 8 ounces Cool Whip. Keep in refrigerator.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar and Butter Buds.
Add baking soda to applesauce.
Add applesauce to Butter Buds mixture; blend well. Sift together the remaining ingredients and add to first mixture. Add raisins and Grape-Nuts.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet sprayed with nonfat cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Yields 9 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Pour liquid over meat, celery and onion after putting in roasting pan.
Cover tightly and bake at 300° for 6 hours.
When done, take fork and break meat up.
Juice will be absorbed and meat will flake apart.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning.
Layer in baking dish tortillas, beef, cheese, olives, onion and sauce.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mom mares bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Combine all ingredients.
Add water, enough to cover ham bone.
Cook slowly several hours (2 to 3), until thickened.
Stir occasionally.

title: apple cider cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream butter well.
Add sugar.
Cream until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add flour mixture with cider.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 350° for an hour.

title: gazpacho (cold soup)
directions: Chop finely all ingredients and chill several hours before serving.

title: strawberry-topped cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, stir together graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press onto the bottom only of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
With an electric mixer, beat undrained cottage cheese until smooth.
Add cream cheese, sugar, flour and 1 teaspoon of the vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add eggs and beat just until combined.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in the 1/4 cup milk.
Pour mixture into pan.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix cranberry cocktail, lemon juice and sugar.
May be mixed day before using.
Mix with ginger ale carefully and pour over sherbet in punch bowl.
Serve in punch cups.
Yields 30 servings.

title: curried cream of pea soup
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove and drain.
Cook all vegetables and garlic except peas in bacon fat until soft.
Add curry and pepper, then 1/2 the chicken stock and peas.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Puree in batches; return to pot.
Whisk in remaining stock and half and half.
Simmer on low until hot.
Ladle into bowls.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: halloween spiders
directions: Melt
chocolate over low heat.	Add noodles.
Mix well. Drop by	spoonful onto wax paper.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated. Good!!!!!!!

title: non-alcoholic eggnog
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Fold in cream.

title: meat loaf for crock-pot
directions: Combine all ingredients, and since I have a small family, I divide it in half with my hands with one half going into the crock-pot on low with a line of ketchup down the middle of the loaf for about 7 or 8 hours.
Serves about 4.
The other half of the mixture goes into the freezer to be used later as great meatballs for spaghetti with meatballs.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add Cheddar cheese, green pepper, onion, pineapple, ground red pepper and Tabasco to cream cheese.
Mix well.
Roll into ball or log shape, then roll in chopped nuts until completely covered.
Chill for at least 24 hours prior to serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and milk for 5 to 10 minutes to form soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow and peanut butter. Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased or buttered dish.

title: mixed-up salt
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a tightly covered jar.
Use to sprinkle over sliced tomatoes, salads, raw and cooked vegetables, salad dressings, bread, etc.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix all together. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix well and cover.
Let rise about 4 hours at room temperature.
Punch down. Cover tightly and put in refrigerator. Use as needed.
Make into rolls.
Set in warm place, covered, and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: morgan county woman's club angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening with mixer. Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Work together with a spoon until all flour is absorbed.
Cover bowl and refrigerate until ready to use.
This dough will keep for weeks.

title: california cocktail dates
directions: Stuff pitted dates with pecan half and wrap with 1/3 slice bacon.
Bake in shallow dish in oven until bacon is crisp.
Drain and serve warm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, milk and syrup.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Add chopped nuts and stir.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Add enough sweet milk to a large frying pan to a depth of about an inch and a half.
Stir in to taste sugar, 1/4 cup butter and flavorings.
Heat to just under boiling point.
Slice peeled potatoes about 1/2 inch thick and let simmer until they are soft. Don't overcook!
Place cooked potatoes in a casserole dish. Continue the process until all potatoes are cooked, adding milk as needed.
When completed, simmer the milk mixture until the desired thickness and pour over potatoes.
Hummmmm good!

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Cover each slice ham with thin layer of cream cheese.
Roll up.
Place toothpick in to hold together.
Place in freezer until cheese is hardened.
Remove from freezer.
Slice into pinwheels. Arrange on tray with a toothpick in each pinwheel.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Pour cooked noodles in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Saute ground beef and pour over noodles.
Pour pizza sauce, cheese and pepperoni and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes,
just enough to melt the cheese.

title: crunchy herbed fish
directions: Mix potatoes, basil, onions, salt and pepper.
Dip fish into egg; coat with potato mixture.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet until hot.
Cook fish over medium heat until golden brown, 5 to 7 minutes on each side.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; let set until foamy. Add the rest of ingredients.
Turn out onto floured board for kneading.
Add 1/2 cup flour to prevent sticking.
Should be earlobe soft.
Allow to double in bulk.
Make 2 balls; press onto greased cookie sheets.
Add sauce and cheese, etc.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 20 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.

title: poppy seed biscuit twists
directions: Roll each biscuit in hands, stretching to 8 inches long. Shape in a loop, pulling one end through center.
Place each biscuit on a greased baking sheet; brush with butter and sprinkle with seed.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: prune bread
directions: Soak prunes overnight; remove seeds and chop fine.
Mix with sugar, shortening, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes and cool.
Beat in eggs, flour, soda and salt.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in loaf pan.

title: salmon sandwich bake
directions: Toast bread and trim crusts.
Mix margarine and mustard, spread over 1 slice of each toast slice.
Arrange 6 slices, buttered side up, in ungreased baking pan.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: brussel sprouts & sweet potatoes
directions: In a 12 inch skillet, cook bacon; drain and reduce heat to low. Add onion and cook 5 minutes. Add sprouts; cook 5 minutes. Transfer to bowl; add salt, pepper and pecans. Add potatoes to pan and cook 3 minutes per side. Whisk together syrup and butter. Toss all ingredients into buttered 2 quart baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Do not drain any fruits.
Freeze in 2 or 3 containers.
Remove from freezer about 30 minutes before serving.
Spoon slush into sherbet dishes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water until tender, drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream, stir in carrots.
Mix stuffing and margarine in separate bowl.
Fold squash mixture into soup mixture.
Pour 1/2 stuffing mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spoon vegetable mixture over top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy bread sticks
directions: Place hot dog buns on a jelly roll pan.
Mix melted margarine, Greek seasoning, dill weed and garlic powder and brush on buns. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 250° until bread is dry, then turn off oven and leave until cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in 5-quart bowl or paper sack.
In 2 1/2-quart bowl, combine the brown sugar, margarine, Karo syrup and salt. Microwave the mixture to a boil on Full power, takes about 3 minutes.
Boil the mixture for 3 minutes, stirring several times. Remove mixture from microwave and stir in baking soda.
Mix well. Pour mixture over popcorn.
Coat evenly.
Put coated popcorn back in microwave and cook 3 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds. Stirring coats popcorn evenly.
As corn cools, it becomes crisp. Store in airtight container.

title: fat-free fruit muffins
directions: Whip Egg Beaters.
Add sugar, applesauce, milk and vanilla. Mix well.
Add pudding mix; mix well.
Add flour, bran, baking powder and cinnamon and mix well.
Add fruit to mixture and fold. Pour into greased (Pam) muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Wesson or Pam.
Put broken up beef in bottom.
Add onions, vegetables, mushrooms and hash browns.
Thin soup with 1 can milk and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is done.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese over top and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: carrot pineapple roast dinner
directions: In a crock-pot, place the carrots. Trim excess fat from the roast.
Fit into crock-pot atop the carrots. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine the pineapple, brown sugar, soy sauce, garlic and basil. Spoon over roast.
Cover and cook on low heat 8 to 10 hours. Remove roast.
Drain carrots and pineapple and reserve cooking liquid.
Return meat, carrots and pineapple to cooker and cover to keep warm. Skim fat from reserved liquid and add water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Pour into saucepan. Blend the water and flour and stir into reserved liquid.
Cook and stir until thickened.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar real well; add flavors to mixture.
Add all flour at once and whipping cream.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Frost.

title: texas brag cake
directions: Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan the pineapple and cherry pie filling and shake ingredients down until even.
Spread box of cake mix over this; sprinkle coconut and nuts over cake mix.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add onion. Add milk and egg, stirring lightly. Drop 1 teaspoon batter for each hush puppy into hot oil. Fry several at a time. Drain on paper towel. Serve while hot. Makes 2 dozen.

title: exotic shrimp
directions: Grate 1 teaspoon lime peel; squeeze 1 tablespoon lime juice. In broiling pan, mix lime peel, juice, garlic, salt, olive oil, cilantro and red pepper.
Add shrimp, tossing to coat well.
Set aside 15 minutes to absorb flavors.
Broil shrimp for 3 minutes. Turn shrimp; broil 3 minutes longer.

title: shortbread scotch
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and mix.
Pat onto cookie sheet.
Prick with a fork.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until light tan color.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in butter until brown. Cook grated squash until tender; drain. Cook macaroni and drain.

Mix 1 can Cheddar cheese soup. (May use mushroom soup and add grated cheese.) Do not dilute soup. Mix all together and put in baking dish. Cover with bread crumbs. Cook 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, oleo and sugar.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.

title: roast chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place onions in a roasting pan, then add chicken.
Sprinkle with seasonings, then drizzle with oil. Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour, then cover and bake an additional 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: strawberry float
directions: Place strawberries in a bowl and mash.
Add sugar until dissolved, put mixture in a jar.
Add milk and close lid tightly. Shake until foamy.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat all ingredients except frosting in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, until moistened. Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently, 2 minutes.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool; frost with Browned Butter Frosting.

title: apricot slush
directions: Add tea bags to boiling water. Simmer for 10 minutes in large container.
Mix the lemonade, orange juice and sugar to the water mixture and stir until dissolved. Add the apricot brandy after this has cooled.
Freeze in plastic container.
To serve, add 3 parts slush to 1 part 7-Up.

title: rose's barbecue beef
directions: Cover beef with sauce.
Cook 1 hour at 425°.
Remove.
Cool. Slice very thin.
Put back in pan with sauce and cook at 350° until tender.
Or mix all together in crock-pot for 8 hours.

title: brown bread
directions: To sour milk, add 1 tablespoon vinegar; let stand 10 minutes. Put Nabisco, salt, sugar, raisins and molasses in a bowl with sour milk.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Mix. Put into greased coffee can.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Layer half of bread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover bread with sliced cream cheese.
Add remaining bread.
Mix together milk, eggs, syrup and spices; pour over bread and cheese in dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with additional syrup and optional toppings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chocolate chips) together and blend with mixer 5 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured (or Pam'ed) Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain thoroughly.
Add
diced onion, green pepper and
drained
red kidney beans.
Add Catalina dressing.
Let set 1 to 2 hours (or overnight).
Before serving, add shredded cheese, sliced tomato and nacho chips.
Toss.

title: rolo cookies
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and egg.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix well. Shape dough around rolo candy.
Make sure candy is completely covered.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 9 minutes or until golden brown.
Take out of oven and flatten with spatula. Cool for 10 minutes and remove from cookie sheet.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole. Cover with 1/2 pretzels.
Top with 1/2 tuna, peas and mushrooms.

title: chili rellano casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper. Lightly grease a deep baking dish.
Add a layer of whole chilies, layer of Jack cheese and then a layer of Cheddar cheese.
Keep alternating layers until dish is at least 3/4 full, then add the beaten eggs.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on your oven. Serve warm with salsa.

title: rich lemon cake
directions: Mix together and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cook for 25 minutes and remove from pan.

title: ice cream cupcakes
directions: Note:
Need 24 to 30 Joy ice cream cups.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Save 2 tablespoons drippings.
Saute onion in drippings 4 to 5 minutes.
Add clam juice and potatoes. Cover and cook over low heat, until potatoes are tender.
Reserve a few pieces of bacon for garnish.
Add remaining bacon, clams, soup, milk and pepper.
Heat and garnish with bacon.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Crush crackers.
Mix with oleo and place half or little more in bottom of dish.
Break chicken into small pieces and place over cracker mixture.
Mix sour cream, soup and broth.
Pour over chicken and put remaining cracker mixture over top.
Bake at 325° to 350° about 45 minutes.

title: raspberry party punch
directions: Place drink mixes in large punch bowl.
Add water and pineapple juice; stir to dissolve.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice.
Makes 29 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in water in saucepan over medium heat about 20 minutes; drain in colander.
Mash and add pepper, salt, carrots and sour cream.
Melt margarine, then pour over stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Use half the stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture on top of stuffing mix layer.
Use rest of stuffing mix as top layer.
Bake at 350° until stuffing mix is lightly browned, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Mix all but pecans.
Shape into ball (cone for a tree) with Saran wrap and refrigerate.
To serve, roll ball in pecans or slice stuffed green olives for tree decorations.
Top with a cinnamon star cookie.

title: red beans & rice
directions: Rinse red beans and pour into a large pot of boiling water. Remove from heat cover and let stand until cool.
Return to heat and cook slowly.
Add chopped onion, parsley, garlic, bay leaf, salt & pepper and sausage to beans.
When beans are tender stir in dark roux made by using vegetable oil and flour.
Cook slowly 20-30 minutes until it's a dark brown color, stirring often. Allow beans to cook about 30 minutes more. Serve hot over rice.

title: two-crust clam pie
directions: Cook diced potatoes and onions together.
When done, add clams and juice, then add thickener (flour and water).
Add margarine. Roll out 1/2 of dough and place on bottom of 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan or large pie plate.
Add other ingredients, except for eggs. Arrange hard-boiled eggs on top of filling.
Roll out and place remaining 1/2 of dough on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Combine water, molasses and baking soda in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients, reserving 1 cup of the crumb mixture.
Mix remaining crumb mixture into the molasses mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top after the first 20 minutes of baking.
Let cool and enjoy with a glass of milk or a cup of coffee.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Pour milk onto cereal.
Wait 6 minutes.
Beat eggs and add to the cereal along with the oil.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased muffin pan and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes clean.

title: homemade play dough(do not eat!!!)
directions: Combine salt, flour and cream of tartar.
Add water and oil. Add food coloring of your choice.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, until consistency of cream puff pastry.
Store in plastic bag.
(Use as you would commercial play dough.)

title: bacon bread
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Mix 1/2 of cheese, onion and bacon with other ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch square or 9-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, onion and bacon.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry crunch salad
directions: Combine pretzel pieces, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Remove and allow to cool thoroughly.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Cook mushrooms, onions and rice in butter for 5 minutes. Place mixture into casserole dish.
Add broth and salt.
Cover and bake at 350° in oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rice pudding
directions: In medium-sized saucepan, combine the milk, rice, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Beat 2 tablespoons of the hot mixture into the eggs, beating constantly.
Stir this mixture into the rice mixture remaining in the saucepan.
Stir in the chopped apple. Cook and stir over low heat for 30 seconds longer.
Do not boil! Remove from heat; stir in the vanilla.
Pour into a large bowl or individual serving dishes.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
The pudding thickens as it chills.
Sprinkle with nuts and serve.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round layer pans (8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally. Pour into pans.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Fill layers with Butterscotch Filling.
Spread Chocolate Chip Glaze over top of cake.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth.
Blend in nuts and marshmallows until coated.
Can spread out in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or drop by spoonfuls.
Refrigerate.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello. Stir and heat.
Let cool.
Pour in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour in medium size Pyrex.

title: brunswick chicken stew
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large Dutch oven; bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove chicken from broth.
Cool chicken completely, skin, bone and coarsely chop meat.

title: bootleg
directions: Put lemonade, lime juice, water and sugar into blender and mix. Add enough mint leaves to fill container.
Mix and strain.
Pour 2 1/2 ounces into a 10-ounce glass and add gin.
Fill glass with ice cubes and soda water.
Serves 6.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato juice and chili beans in a large pot; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add chili powder; bring to a boil.
Serve hot.

title: snicker cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: browniest
directions: Melt chocolate in a glass custard cup in microwave oven 1 1/2 to 2 minutes at High. Cool. Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition. Add vanilla extract and cooled chocolate; mix well. Blend flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into creamed mixture. Mix in nuts. Turn batter into a greased 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish. Cook, uncovered, in microwave oven 7 or 8 minutes at Medium-high or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean. Rotate dish one-quarter turn once. Set dish on flat surface. Cool, then cut into bars. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: mushroom-liver pate
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter in a skillet over medium heat until tender.
Combine mushrooms, braunschweiger and next 5 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon into a buttered 1 3/4-cup mold.
Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold onto a serving platter.
Garnish, if desired. Serve with crackers.
Yield:
1 3/4 cups.

title: yum-yum chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts, remove skin and cut in bite size pieces (or leave whole).
Layer chicken in a well-greased casserole dish. Mix soups and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Spread Stove Top dressing over this.
Melt oleo with broth and package of dressing mix spices and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low calorie cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, green peppers, and onions.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss lightly.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Add onion to broccoli.
Cook rice fully.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Top with additional cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly throughout.

title: polish reuben casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion and mustard in medium bowl; blend well.
Spread sauerkraut in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with uncooked noodles.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over top.
Top with sausage, then cheese.
Combine crumbs in butter in small bowl. Sprinkle over top.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until noodles are tender. Garnish as desired.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 2 layers of sliced potatoes. Brown hamburger and drain.
Add soup to beef.
Pour over potatoes. Spread tomato sauce over mixture, then sprinkle with oregano.

title: dumplngs
directions: Mix thoroughly and wet with 1 cup milk.
Drop from spoon.

title: upside-down pumpkin cake
directions: Combine all but cake mix, nuts and margarine.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Sprinkle cake mix over top. Sprinkle nuts and drizzle margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Combine ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin pans coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: If pink punch is desired, add some strawberries and red food coloring.

title: noel nut balls
directions: Mix butter or margarine, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add flour. Mix in 2 cups nuts.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 325° until done. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, oatmeal, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Combine all together; add 12 ounces chocolate chips and 1 cup nuts (optional).
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. (Won't be chewy if baked too long.)

title: meaty potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender; mash.
Do not drain. Melt oleo.
Add onion.
Cook until golden.
Add flour and blend. Add seasonings, milk and potatoes.
Cook until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Add wieners.
Serves 6.

title: guacamole
directions: Scoop avocado out of shell and mash with fork; squeeze lime juice for flavor as well as to prevent it from browning too quickly.
Add picante sauce, I usually put 2 or 3 tablespoons, but add to your own liking and consistency preference.
Add salt, pepper and a shake of garlic powder; stir and serve immediately with tostada chips.

title: corned beef and cabbage with vegetables
directions: Melt butter in a large pan. Cut cabbage into large pieces. Place in pan. Add carrots, onion and potatoes. Add salt and pepper.
Break corned beef on top.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: easy butterscotch chip chocolate cookie
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in morsels and pecans.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are just set.
Let stand for 2 minutes, remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti by package directions.
Add sauce and mushrooms and mix in spaghetti.
Put in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Put bread crumbs, mixed with melted butter, on top.
Bake at 400° until bubbly and crumbs are brown.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix together egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Coat pork chops on both sides with egg mixture.
Roll in crushed croutons.
Place on baking sheet.
Put in oven, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Turn, cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes more.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Saute onions in butter in skillet and add cheese spread, sour cream and milk. Blend well.
Stir in carrots and spoon into a greased casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until hot.

title: etoufee(a-two-fay)
directions: Saute all vegetables in margarine.
Add cream of celery soup (undiluted).
Add all spices and sauces; stir and simmer for at least one hour.
Stir occasionally.
About a half hour before your are ready to serve, add the main ingredient and simmer until done. Remove bay leaves.
Serve with cooked rice.
This recipe freezes well.

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs. Then add in sour cream and vanilla. Then add in flour, powder, soda and salt. Mix in chocolate chips until well combined. Spread into greased 11 x 13 pan.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix together in large bowl all ingredients.
Press mixture into 2 (8-inch) square pans.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into small pieces and dip into dipping chocolate.
Place pieces on a cookie sheet (covered with wax paper) and allow chocolate to harden. Store in refrigerator or in a cool place.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening. Add egg and pineapple; mix together.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together sauerkraut, bean sprouts, green pepper, onion and pimentos.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over the sauerkraut mixture.

title: lemon jello cake and glaze
directions: Mix in bowl and pour into greased oblong pan.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple jam
directions: In a large kettle, bring the zucchini and sugar to a boil. Boil and stir constantly for 6 minutes.
Add the lemon juice and pineapple.
Cook and stir for 8 minutes.
Add gelatin.
Stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Skim off any foam.
Fill jars or plastic containers.
Cool before covering with lids.
Refrigerate up to 3 weeks.
Yields 8 1/2 cups.

title: sausage balls
directions: Shred cheese.
Add biscuit mix, and uncooked sausage.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields:
Bake, freeze and reheat.

title: creamy shake
directions: Pour half of milk and ice cream in blender.
Mix until smooth. Add half of cream cheese and one orange (peeled).
Blend until well mixed.
Pour mixture into a pitcher.
Repeat the same thing with remaining ingredients.
Pour all of mixture together into pitcher and stir.
Serve at once.

title: potatoes with spicy italian sausage
directions: Remove the skin from the sausages and break up the meat. Heat the oil in a large cast-iron skillet.
Add the meat, onion and potatoes.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: chicken creole
directions: Heat oven to
Spray a large baking pan with oil. Put flour, salt,
pepper,
paprika
and
poultry
seasoning in plastic bag.
Shake chicken,
3 pieces at a time.
Put in pan. Bake 25 to 30	minutes. Remove chicken from pan.
Add rice and vegetables to pan.
Put chicken on top of rice mix. Bring to a boil the chicken broth,
tomatoes
and
rest of seasoning (hot sauce to taste). Pour
over	chicken and rice, covering both. Bake, uncovered, 40 to 50
minutes. Add more liquid (water) to prevent dryness.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash brown potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, onion, 1/2 cup butter, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Top with crumbled corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: ma ma's brisket
directions: Let brisket stand overnight in liquid smoke, vinegar, sugar and water.
Turn once or twice.
Baste and cook at 275° for 5 hours or until done.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Cut loaf lengthwise.
Combine tomato paste, Parmesan cheese, onion, olives, oregano, salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add meat; mix well.
Spread atop loaf halves.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with tomato slices and green pepper rings.
Sprinkle cheese atop tomatoes.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter and cream together.
Add the sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla and beat until smooth and set aside.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Pour half the brownie batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour all the cream cheese mixture over brownie layer.
Spoon remaining brownie batter in spots over cream cheese layer and swirl together with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost if you wish.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and peel.
Mix vinegar and water; bring to a boil. Add sugar. Remove from fire.
Add garlic, onion, sweet pepper, bay leaves and spices of your choice.
Pour over eggs and let sit a couple of days. Cut eggs in half to serve.

title: quick and easy chicken salad
directions: Toast almonds on a baking sheet for 6 to 8 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and let cool. Cut grapes in half. Mix chicken, grapes, almonds and yogurt along with pepper. Chill.

title: coconut icing
directions: In a saucepan combine flour, salt, and milk.
Heat stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool completely.
Cream sugar, oil, and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in flour mixture.
Add nuts and coconut.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; chill.
Beat softened cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding as per box directions using only 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top and serve.

title: roast turkey
directions: Thaw turkey.
Remove giblet and wash.
Rub lightly with butter.
Place turkey in roasting pan.
Add pickling spices to water and pour over turkey and into roasting pan.
Bake according to weight.
Keep pan covered until about the last hour of baking. Baste every 30 minutes with spice and water mixture.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: In large saucepan of boiling water, simmer ribs about 5 minutes to remove excess fat.
Drain in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add ribs and marinate 2 to 3 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes.
Increase temperature to 450° and continue baking 5 to 10 minutes or until very tender.

title: crabapple pickles
directions: Wash crabapples; do not remove stems.
Pickle crabapples as soon as possible after picking before they become mellow.
Make a syrup by boiling remaining ingredients for 3 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in mashed banana.
Stir together plain flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture and mix until well blended.
Bake in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: great fried fish
directions: Beat egg, mustard and water in shallow pan.
Combine meal, flour and cheese in another dish.
Dip fillets first in egg mixture, then meal mixture.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes on each side. Salt and pepper.

title: lemon cake
directions: Bake the first 6 ingredients 20 minutes at 350°.
With fork, punch holes in cake.
Put mixture of powdered sugar and lemon juice over cake.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: italian breaded chicken breast
directions: Beat chicken with meat mallet; salt and pepper chicken.
Dip chicken in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Brown in melted butter on both sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn after first 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, beef, beans, avocado, onion, cheese and tomatoes in a large bowl.
When ready to serve, pour in salad dressing and nachos.
Mix and serve immediately.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: In a small bowl mix ingredients together.
Spread mayonnaise mixture evenly over peas.
Cover dish and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Puree shrimp in blender; add remaining ingredients.

title: no bake peanut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips.
Press into 9 x 13 pan. Melt chips in microwave, about 4 minutes at 50% power.
Spread over top and chill.
Cut into bars after 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate chipper cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, vanilla, Frangelico and Tia Maria until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt, gradually adding to the creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Place in storage container and refrigerate overnight.

title: arizona salad
directions: Drain oranges.
Combine cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Stir in oranges.
Fold in whipped topping.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Chill slightly before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put biscuits in bag with cup of sugar and cinnamon and shake until biscuits are coated.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes in greased Bundt pan.
Take out and pour 1 stick butter and 2 tablespoons of water over and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Do not drain corn.
Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan (9 x 13-inch for thinner casserole).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until edges brown and center is solid.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Mince the garlic.
Shell and devein shrimp, leaving tails on. In a large frying pan, melt butter in the oil over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring occasionally, until just cooked through.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes 10 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain and let cool.
Combine potatoes, onions and pimento in a large bowl. Combine mayonnaise and next 7 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Add to potato mixture, tossing gently to coat.
Cover and chill.
Serves 4.

title: carolina corn dog surprise
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg and milk together and add dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Insert popsicle sticks into franks which have been wiped with dry cloth and dusted with flour. Dip into batter and drop into oil heated to 375°.
Fry until brown and drain on paper towel.
Serve piping hot.
Catsup and mustard may be brushed on before eating.

title: wilsie fortner's brown sugar pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients together.	Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and mix well (will be thick).
Add eggs (one at a time), beating well after each addition.
Mix in carrots.
Pour in 3 (8-inch) pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ma's pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, add ingredients in sequence, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into two 9-inch pie-crust filled pie tins. Bake on top shelf at 425° for 10 minutes.
Bake on middle shelf at 350° for 50 minutes.
Pies are done when tip of knife comes out fairly smooth.

title: margaret stansbury's chile rellenos casserole
directions: Wash chiles; remove seeds and dry on paper towels.
Cut cheese into strips.
Beat eggs in 2 cup measuring cup; add flour and salt and beat until smooth.
Add milk until mixture is almost to the 2 cup line.
Mix with beater thoroughly.
Line bottom of greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch) with chiles.
Cover with strips of cheese.
Repeat layer.
Pour egg mixture over chiles and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until custard is baked and top is golden brown.

title: goodie applesauce cake
directions: Sift together first 8 ingredients.
Add the rest of the ingredients, beating well, at least
for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 7 1/2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with your favorite lemon frosting.
Makes 18 servings.

title: mustard sauce dip
directions: Mix mustard and cider vinegar. Cover and let sit overnight. The next day, cook with beaten egg, salt and sugar.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Pour over cream cheese. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: talerine
directions: Saute onions
and
bell
peppers
in
fat
and then add ground beef,
salt
and
pepper and chili powder.	Cook for 10 minutes and
then add tomatoes, tomato paste and tomato sauce. Cook for 15 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, milk, flour and beaten eggs and cook until thickened.
Take from stove; add butter, coconut and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover top with toasted coconut and whipped cream.

title: baked tuna ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in a greased foil lined 8-inch ring mold (5 cup capacity).
Bake 50 to 60 minutes (until set).
Invert on a platter.
Fill center with buttered lima beans or green beans.

title: tangy bean salad(black-eyed pea)
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, onion and green pepper.
Drain peas well and add to dressing.
Add pimientos; garnish with onion rings if desired.
Marinate in refrigerator 4 hours and serve. Great for picnics, holidays, any get together.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with apples, nuts and dates.
Stir together.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla all at once.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch square pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer ingredients, in the order listed, in medium-large baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil.
Add soda and water.
Add dry ingredients.
Divide in 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: basil pot restaurant whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix dry and wet ingredients separately, then combine, mixing only until moist.
Spices are optional.
Grease tin.
Bake in muffin tin in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: church dessert
directions: Mix together cookies and margarine; set aside 1/2 cup for topping.
Spread remainder of cookie mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze.
Spread peppermint ice cream on top of crust; freeze.
Spread fudge topping on top of ice cream; freeze.
Spread Cool Whip on top of fudge topping and sprinkle with the reserved 1/2 cup of cookie crumbs; freeze.
Take out of freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: bean and turkey skillet dinner(low cholesterol)
directions: In a large skillet, add oil when hot.
Add onions and carrots. Stir-fry about 5 minutes.
Add turkey and stir-fry, breaking up turkey until done.
Add tomato sauce, oregano, beans and pepper. Stir-fry another minute or so, until all ingredients are very hot. Stir in parsley then serve.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in electric ice cream freezer. To make peach ice cream just add to the above ingredients 5 to 6 peaches and 8 oz. peach soda (any brand). Blend peaches and soda together in blender and pour in ice cream mixture.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Layer in a greased casserole dish hamburger mixture, sliced potatoes. Top off with green beans. Mix soup with 1/4 c. water and pour over beans. Bake approx. 35-40 minute at 350 degrees.

title: bath salts
directions: Mix in jumbo canister and put in small containers.
Wrap in net and give for an instant gift.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until tender.
Slice and layer in buttered casserole with sliced pepper and pimento.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Melt butter.
Add flour and stir until well blended.
Gradually add milk.
Add cheeses that have been cubed and stir until melted.
Pour mixture over potatoes and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup together. Bring to a hard boil. Then add peanuts and cook on medium-high for about 20 or more minutes. Then take off stove and stir in the soda as fast as possible and pour onto greased cookie sheets.
Don't spread, tilt the pans and cool; break into small pieces.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Defrost berries according to package directions.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and berries, beating until light. Mix flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg and salt. Blend flour mixture into strawberry mixture just until flour is moistened.
Do not overmix.
Pour into greased 9 1/2 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan. Finish cooling on rack.

title: three bean salad
directions: Rinse kidney, wax and green beans well.
Let drain well.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over beans.
Mix together in a bowl and refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Mix egg whites until stiff; gradually add sugar.
Mix nuts, crackers and baking powder; blend all together and spread in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: date nut roll
directions: Reserve 1/4 crumbs.
Mix above ingredients together.
Place remaining crumbs on wax paper; roll the mixture in the crumbs until they are absorbed.

title: good old virginia sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients at high speed with mixer.
Add flavors.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: dump-it cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Dump applesauce into it.
Dump crushed pineapple on top.
Spread dry cake mix over the pineapple. Melt butter or margarine and pour it on top of the cake mix. Sprinkle nuts over the melted butter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: cherry whip delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Spread cherry or blueberry pie filling on top.
Chill.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl; make well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugar, cornstarch and salt. Stir in water and place over direct heat.
Add egg yolks and stir until thick. Cool 3 minutes and add lemon juice.
Can cover with meringue and bake at 325°
until slightly brown, 18 to 20 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake cornbread and cool. Crumble cornbread and blend with remaining ingredients. This keeps in refrigerator several days and is a nice alternative to potato or macaroni salad.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except cereal; set aside.
Blend other ingredients.
Add to dry mixture and stir.
Add cereal.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be refrigerated to make later or freeze baked muffins.
Makes 50.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain the fat.
Place meat in crock-pot or Dutch oven.
Add all the other ingredients and cook until all the vegetables are cooked through.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Cook rice, celery and onion together.
Add cooked chicken, cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Mix.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes and slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all this together and stir well.
Let set overnight before serving.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Spread oleo, brown sugar, pineapple and pie filling in 9 x 15-inch pan.
Make yellow cake following directions on box except use juice from pineapple and the pina colada mix for liquid (add water to make the difference).
Bake as directed.
Let stand 5 minutes, then turn out upside down on tray.
Serves 15.

title: quick dinner salad
directions: Prepare rice following package directions.
Drain bean salad, reserving 1/2 cup marinade.
For dressing, combine reserved marinade, oil, salt, black and red peppers.
Combine drained bean salad, rice, onion and cheese in bowl.
Add dressing and vinegar. Refrigerate.

title: martha patch's crab pie with swiss
directions: Sprinkle cheese over bottom of pastry shell.
Top with crabmeat and sprinkle with green onions.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, cream, lemon peel and mustard.
Mix well.
Pour over crabmeat.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife comes away clean from center of pie.
Let stand a bit before slicing.
I serve with salad or fruit and crackers or hot rolls.
Corn muffins go really well with it.

title: coconut delight
directions: Roll crackers in plastic bag until fine crumbs.
Melt margarine and add to crackers in pan.
Mix together and pat to mold.
Put in refrigerator to set for 1 hour.

title: feather pancakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix very well.
Cook on hot greased griddle.

title: fish in beer batter
directions: Place flour, beer, egg, baking powder and salt in bowl; beat lightly.
Dip fish in batter to coat.
Cook in pan containing hot shortening until done and brown.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make a syrup from the pineapple juice, sugar and boiling water.
Add the syrup, grapefruit juice, cold water, cold tea and sparkling water.
In a large punch bowl, put the mixture together and float the lemons and oranges in it.
Serves 40 to 50 people.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop vegetables and mix together.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar together and pour over vegetable mixture.
Just before serving, fold in bacon and cheese.

title: bacon roll-ups(may be prepared ahead of time)
directions: Melt butter in water in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir into stuffing, then add egg and sausage.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill for about an hour for easier handling, then shape into small oblongs about the size of pecans.

Cut bacon strips into thirds crosswise. Wrap one piece around dressing mixture and fasten with wooden pick. Place on rack in shallow pan and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown and crisp, turning at halfway point in cooking.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.
May be made the day before baking. Also freezes well before baking.
Yield:
about 36 appetizers.
(I usually double this.)

title: pasta with italian sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in frying pan.
Pour in stewed tomatoes, garlic and olives.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and let simmer until sauce is thick.

title: savory roasted onions
directions: In a shallow baking dish, place your onions.
Spray lightly with the olive oil spray.
Place the onions, cut side down, and bake at 350°, until tender, about 50 minutes.
When hot out of the oven, sprinkle with vinegar and parsley.
This will serve 4 deliciously.

title: yummy goodies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into greased miniature muffin pans, filling 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: In medium saucepan, add sugar and flour; mix.
Add vinegar and beet juice.
Stir over medium heat until thick.
Add butter; stir to melt.
Add beets (drained).
Stir and simmer until done.
Add salt, if desired.

title: beet summer delight(serves 4)
directions: In large skillet, simmer oil, garlic and anchovies, stirring gently.
Remove from heat when garlic is golden and set aside. Add beets with its juice, parsley, chopped escarole, salt and pepper.
Let all ingredients marinate while cooking spaghettini.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, flour, salt, oil and vanilla together.
Mix in slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle pecans over filling.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Mix sugar and salad dressing.
Spread over top of layers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Crumble bacon over top before serving (bacon bits may be used).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: skinny chili
directions: Brown beef or turkey and onion with salt. Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 30 minutes over medium heat.
A very good diet meal.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl, then add wet ingredients.
Stir (do not beat).
Bake in 3 layers in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool thoroughly.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: willard's grandmother's applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add flour, salt, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon; mix well.
Add raisins, applesauce and baking powder; stir all together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with a butter frosting.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix sugar, cream, water, butter and Karo syrup.
Cook to soft boiling stage.
Add dates; stir until dissolved.
Cool a little. Beat until creamy, add nuts.
Beat and pour out on damp cloth. Roll in damp cloth and refrigerate.

title: chicken delight
directions: Skin, wash and dry chicken so jam will stick.
Arrange in flat casserole dish, coat with jam, then with dressing.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.
Baste often when uncovered.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts together.
Make two balls or one large ball.
Roll cheese balls in chopped pecans.
Wrap and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve so it will be firm. Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed chicken thighs
directions: Cook bacon in small pan over low heat until crisp (about 10 minutes).
Remove bacon; crumble and set aside.
Pour off drippings, except for 2 tablespoons (reserve for later).
Add celery and onion to drippings left in pan.
Saute for 5 minutes or until soft.
Remove from heat; add sherry, poultry seasoning, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, bread crumbs and bacon.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.

title: caramel icing
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugars, milk and oleo and boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla, stirring well.
Spread on cake.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together until it gets thick.
Start with wafers, then 2 or 3 bananas next.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and pudding together.
Put 1/2 of this mixture on wafers and bananas. Put another layer of wafers, then rest of bananas.
Put remaining pudding, etc. over this.
Use a large dish or pan (a 9 x 13-inch works good).
Mash a few vanilla wafers real fine and sprinkle on top.

title: sweet potato pie(century old recipe)
directions: Put potatoes in a large mixing bowl.
While warm, on low speed, add butter, then add egg, sugar, milk and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake in moderate oven until filing is set and begins to brown.

title: shrimp jambalaya with smoked sausage
directions: Brown onions in oil until really dark, adding small amount of water at a time. Add sausage and fry 3 or 4 minutes. Add celery, green pepper and garlic. Keep adding small amounts of water until wilted. Add parsley and shallots; cook until wilted. Add shrimp; cover and cook for 15 minutes. Add rice and water. Season with salt to taste. Add Worcestershire sauce and Creole seasoning. Bring to a boil, then lower heat. Cook about 1/2 hour or until rice is tender.

title: eggplant and friends
directions: Layer eggplant, onion, zucchini, yellow squash, green pepper, sliced tomatoes and grated cheese in large casserole, sprinkling seasoning 2 or 3 times during layering. Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for at least 45 minutes. Serves about 6 persons.

title: crumb topped tomatoes(microwave)
directions: Cut slice off stem end of each tomato and discard.
Place tomatoes, cut side up, in circle on microproof plate.
Combine onion soup mix, melted butter, crumbs, parsley and basil.
Divide among 4 tomatoes, spreading mixture on cut surface.
Cook, uncovered, on High (Maximum power) 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until tomatoes are hot.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Brown sausage; drain.
Layer sausage and cheese on top of bread.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, and mustard.
Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: miniature quiche
directions: Cream together cheese, butter and cayenne.
Add flour and mix into a smooth dough.
Wrap and chill for an hour or freeze for 30 minutes.
Then form into 48 (1-inch) balls and press into miniature muffin tins.
Place 1/2 teaspoon filling in center of each quiche and then one tablespoon custard.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from tins.
Serve warm.
You may freeze and reheat.

title: cheese custard pie(switzerland)
directions: When pie crust is cool, brush with egg white.
Scald milk or cream.
Reduce heat and add grated cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted, then add salt, paprika, onion and cayenne pepper.
Remove mixture from heat and beat in 3 eggs, one at a time.
Fill pie crust and bake at 325° in a preheated oven until firm (about 45 minutes).

title: gone with the wind
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add sugar and lemon juice and let thicken.
Beat canned milk 10 minutes or until thick.
Add jello. Pour into either a cake pan or individual cups.
Chill until set.

title: mini chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in mini chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake bars
directions: Spray baking pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over bottom of pan; set aside.
In a blender, combine tofu, cream cheese, eggs, noncaloric sweetener, water, cocoa powder and vanilla. Cover and blend until smooth, stopping and scraping sides as necessary.
Pour over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Cool.
In small saucepan, heat preserves over low heat until melted.
Drizzle over bars.
Makes 24 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Dice apples.
Pour on sugar, salt and vanilla.
Set aside. Mix flour, cinnamon, soda, oil, eggs, coconut and walnuts.
Add to apples.
Bake in greased and floured cake pan at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: oatmeal nut muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the oats and nuts. Combine the milk, egg, margarine, molasses and syrup.
Mix with dry ingredients just enough to moisten flour.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for about 5 minutes.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 to 60 minutes. (Watch, will brown on top.)

title: wild rice and pepper salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Cool. Combine salad dressing, oil, black pepper and peel.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly. Serve at room temperature or chilled. Makes 6 servings.

title: soda cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and margarine; add sour milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Sift dry ingredients and mix to a stiff dough.
Roll on floured board about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters. Sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake at 325° until done (10 to 12 minutes).
For added interest, coloring and cocoa may be mixed into dough.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Cook and remove excess fat. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, pepper, oregano, sweet basil and garlic salt.
Stir and simmer 20 minutes.

title: alligator stew
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover pot. Cook over medium heat for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sidewalk chalk
directions: Mix plaster of Paris and water.
Place roll on end of wax paper.
Spoon mixture into roll.
Let cure for 24 hours before using.

title: toasted coconut orange pie
directions: Bring orange juice, water and sugar to a boil. Add pudding mix and boil 1 minute. Stir in orange extract.
Cool 10 minutes.
Pour into pastry shell. Refrigerate 3 hours.
Decorate with whipped cream and toasted coconut.

title: crabmeat mornay(appetizer)
directions: Melt butter in heavy pot.
Saute onions and parsley.
Blend in flour, half and half and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted. Add other ingredients; gently fold in crabmeat.

title: basting sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into jar.
Stir well and slice enough cucumbers to fill jar.
Will be good to eat in one week. You can keep adding pickles as these are used.
Stir once in the middle of the week.
These are really good!

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, flour, milk and rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie crust (1 large or 2 small shells).

title: standard yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water or follow directions on package.
In large bowl combine sugar, shortening and salt.
Stir in hot milk. Cool to lukewarm.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Brown roast if desired.
Put roast in crock-pot.
Add salt and pepper.
Add garlic powder to taste.
Cover with onion soup; cook on low 8 to 9 hours.
Pour off soup for thickened gravy.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until browned.
Drain; set aside. Separate dough into eight triangles.
Arrange on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form sides.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is hot, poke holes in it and pour sweetened condensed milk over cake.
Let cool, then pour caramel topping over it. Frost with whipped topping.
Crush toffee bars and sprinkle over cake.
Add toasted almonds and maraschino cherries.

title: almond crunch
directions: Put foil on cookie sheet and butter.
On medium heat, put all ingredients in a pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until you get the color you want (medium brown).
Remove from heat.
Pour out onto foil and spread.
Let cool and break up.

title: portuguese coffee buttercake
directions: Beat butter in bowl until smooth.
Beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
Beat in flour and salt, just until combined.

title: butter pecan ice cream cake
directions: Mix crushed Ritz crackers and melted butter together.
Put in oblong cake pan and pat out evenly for crust.
Mix ice cream, butter pecan instant pudding and milk.
Pour on crust.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed pecans.

title: granny's tea cakes
directions: Mix dough as biscuit dough.
Roll out on floured surface to the thickness of pastry.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: betty glasgow's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together. Add to first mixture and mix.
Drop by spoonful in little balls on cookie sheet.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnuts. Secure with toothpicks. Put in 425° oven until bacon is crisp. Drain off all grease.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes and drain.
Discard juices.
Grind peppers. Combine celery seed, sugar and vinegar.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add to vegetables.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Cold pack about 20 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Tie spices
in a bag and add to vinegar and sugar, etc. Simmer 15
minutes
before
adding beets.
Then heat through, about 5 minutes.

title: russian or spiced tea
directions: Mix well all ingredients and store in one pound can or glass jar.
To serve: Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup or as desired and add boiling water and stir.

title: sour cream cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter in bowl; mix well.
Press over bottom and side of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill in refrigerator.
Combine cream cheese, 1 3/4 cups sugar, flour, vanilla and lemon rind in mixer bowl; mix well.
Add eggs and egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add whipping cream and beat until well blended.
Pour into chilled crust.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 250°.
Bake for 1 hour longer.
Loosen from rim of pan.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Remove rim of spring-form pan.
Chill in refrigerator for 3 hours to overnight.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: vegetable saute
directions: Chop and mash vegetables.
Fry onion and spices.
Add cauliflower and potatoes.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add peas and zucchini.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Serve over brown rice.
Serves 8.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix crushed pineapple, cream cheese and powdered sugar until blended well.
Add Cool Whip and nuts. Put into 9-inch graham cracker crust.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, saving 2 tablespoons of juice.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
