Add vinegar and beet juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add beets and butter; heat.

title: non-alcoholic eggnog fruit bread
directions: Combine in sifter the flour, baking powder, spices, salt and sugar.
Sift into mixing bowl.
Stir in pecans and fruit.
Combine eggs, eggnog and melted butter or margarine.
Add to dry ingredients, only mixing until ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, greased and slightly floured, and bake in a 350° oven for about 70 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Glaze.

title: layered green pea salad
directions: Layer salad ingredients in a glass bowl, beginning with lettuce, then tomato wedges, sliced boiled eggs, shredded cheese, diced onion and green peas, then adding another layer of large lettuce leaves over top.
Cover completely with about 1/4 inch thick layer of the Miracle Whip to seal over top.
Sprinkle bacon bits over this.
Serves 12 people.

title: funnel cake
directions: Use deep fryer or skillet.
Don't pour to much oil.
Have oil hot, but don't burn it.
Hold funnel over oil and move in a circular motion and then crisscross as you pour batter.

title: potato dish
directions: While potatoes are cooking, combine soup, milk, onion, cheese and pimento.
Place a layer of potatoes in a casserole dish; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with half of the soup mixture.
Add another layer of potatoes, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Pour rest of soup mixture over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Beat 2 minutes.
Butter a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer graham crackers in pan, then 1/2 pudding mixture. Top with graham crackers, remaining pudding and another layer of crackers.

title: si-mi fruit cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream.
Add 3/4 cup flour.
Mix well.
Add cocoa and rest of sour cream. Beat well.
Add nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Mix.
Bake in layers and cover with icing of powdered sugar and butter or cream cheese.

title: peach preserves
directions: Peel peaches and remove seeds.
Cut each peach into 6 to 8 pieces.
Combine sugar and water and boil 5 minutes.
Add peaches and boil slowly, uncovered, until fruit is clear and juice is thick.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal while hot.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Add coffee and vanilla; beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Batter will be thin.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes for the 13 x 9-inch pan or 28 to 30 minutes for 9-inch pans.
This is great with a 7-Minute Frosting, but my family loves chocolate fudge frosting.

title: deviled mock drumsticks
directions: Beat 1 egg and add to white sauce.
Add Worcestershire sauce, parsley, onion, salt, Tabasco sauce and turkey.
Mix well.
Shape into drumsticks.
Beat 1 egg and add water.
Roll drumsticks alternately in egg, crumbs, egg and crumbs, ending with crumbs. Deep fry at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes depending on size of drumsticks.
Insert wooden skewers for serving and easy handling. Good way to use leftover turkey.

title: picnic barbecues
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add beef, celery and onion. Brown, stirring often.
Turn burner to low and add chili sauce and salt.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour.

title: zucchini sausage pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Press liquid from zucchini between double layers of paper towels.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake pie crust 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce oven temperature to 375°.
Pour mixture from bowl into pie crust.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes clean.
Let stand for at least 10 minutes before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Put vanilla in milk and set aside.
Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk a little at a time, beginning and ending with flour.
Grease and flour pan (tube).
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients and set aside.
In a larger bowl, mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add dry mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: You may add other fresh fruits, if your desire.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together as if making a fruitcake.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.
Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: baking dough
directions: Mix salt and flour and stir in water and glycerine (which has been premixed).
Knead on a floured board for about 10 minutes. If it is too dry, moisten hands and knead in water or if too wet, add a little flour.
Can be kept in refrigerator in plastic bags for several days.
After the children have formed their creations, place them on an oiled cookie sheet and bake at 250° for up to 3 hours, depending on the thickness.
Bake until hard.
When cool, spray with a plastic or varnish finish or let children paint with tempera paint and then spray.
These make good gifts.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Makes 1 punch bowl full.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onions just before meat is browned. Drain excess oil.
Add soups, rice, pepper and soy sauce.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Boil flour and water until thick.
Cool.
Beat oleo and sugar until well mixed.
Add flour mixture; beat until fluffy.

title: pecan delights
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and shortening well.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Sift flour; measure and add to creamed mixture with salt and vanilla, mixing well.
Form into small balls, about 1 teaspoon of dough to each ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or just lightly browned.
Roll, while hot, in powdered sugar and again when cold.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Season 2 1/2-quarts water with 3 tablespoons salt, then add ingredients, except the shrimp, 4 onions and bay leaves.
Bring to boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and bring to boil; simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool; devein shrimp.
In large pan, arrange the shrimp in layers with 4 medium onions and bay leaves.
Pour over each layer the following sauce.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix all ingredients except margarine and crackers.
Place in greased casserole that you have sprayed with cooking oil.
Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs and place on top.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.
Recipe can be doubled for a large casserole dish.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice evenly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Mix mushroom soup and water; pour over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over everything. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix filling in a large bowl until smooth.
Put in pie shells.
Bake 55 minutes.
Let cool on wire rack until cool.
Garnish with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: taco franks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cheese, chips, onion and salsa. Stuff each dog with 1/4 cup of mixture. Place in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Enjoy!

title: beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place brisket in roasting pan; cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 3 hours or until soft, checking halfway through to see if you need to add any water (but you shouldn't).
If not for immediate consumption, allow brisket to cool, then slice.
Return meat to gravy for reheating.

title: spanish rice(quick-easy-cheap)
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Cook rice.
Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meatballs italienne
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine egg, milk, onion, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and pepper.
Add ground beef, oats and cheese, mixing well.
Shape into 1 3/4-inch balls (about 2 tablespoons of meat mixture each).
Place in shallow baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes or until no longer pink in center, turning balls over after 10 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Add to heated spaghetti sauce.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ground beef potato supreme casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Thaw potatoes and combine all ingredients, except cornflakes.
Stir well.
Melt butter in one large or 2 medium casseroles.
Take 2 to 3 cups crushed cornflakes and sprinkle on top.
Dot with margarine and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
You may have to put a piece of foil on top toward the last 1/2 hour to keep the cornflakes from getting too brown. Freezes well uncooked to prepare a make-ahead meal.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk in large bowl.
Pour in lemon juice and mix well.
Add pineapple and chopped pecans.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: broccoli with rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until vegetables are clear. Cook broccoli; drain well. Mix broccoli with soup and cheese. Add to celery and onion.
Stir in rice. Season and mix well. Put in greased casserole and top with stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend soft margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add sour cream and mashed bananas.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Blend in slowly.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut into chunks.
To each jar add 3 or 4 slices of onion, 2 pieces of celery and 2 heads of dill.
Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar and water; bring to a boil.
Place cucumbers in jars, then cover with hot sugar, salt, vinegar and water solution.
Seal at once.
For best results do not use for 30 days.

title: chocolate cherry angel cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
At high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar (one tablespoon at a time), until stiff and glossy.
Add almond extract.
In a small bowl mix flour and cocoa.
Sprinkle over egg whites, half at a time.
Using rubber spatula, gently fold in.
Spoon into 8-inch tube pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Invert cake.
Cool in pan.
Remove.
Cut into 3 layers. Spread with jam.
Frost with whipped topping and cherries.
Makes 16 servings.
Contains 84 calories per serving.

title: jigglers
directions: In large bowl, stir gelatin in boiling water for 3 minutes until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Dip bottom of pan in warm water about 15 seconds.
Cut with cookie cutters or in squares.
Lift from pan and enjoy!

title: pound cake
directions: Add baking powder and salt to flour.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs and beat well; add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla; beat until well mixed.
Cover with Saran Wrap (or aluminum foil) tightly and put in refrigerator overnight.
Put in cold pan, floured and greased, the night you mix the cake and put in cold oven.
Then set oven temperature to 325°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door until near the end of the baking period.
You can also leave this cake in the refrigerator until the next night before you bake, if it is more convenient.
Follow instructions carefully.

title: snicker bar ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars in top of double boiler with a little milk. Beat eggs and condensed milk.
Add half and half into gallon freezer.
Fill with milk.
Freeze.

title: double crunchie
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream together next 5 ingredients Mix together dry and creamed ingredients Add corn flakes, oats and coconut.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls and flatten onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool on racks.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Press rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°; mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion and dill.
Spread on top of cool crust.
Top with mixture of vegetables all chopped very fine. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and refrigerate.
Cut into 1 to 2-inch squares; serve for party or appetizers.

title: plain rice - japanese style
directions: Place the rice in a colander and put it in a bowl of water. Wash rice by stirring it with your hand.
The water will become cloudy.
Empty the bowl, then fill it with fresh water.
Repeat process several times, until the water runs almost clear.
Let the rice drain in the colander for about 30 minutes.

Put the rice and water in a deep, heavy pot; cover and let sit for 30 minutes. Cook over medium heat until the water boils, then reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, making sure the water doesn't boil over. Cook the rice over low heat for another 10 to 12 minutes, then remove the pot from the heat and let sit for 10 to 15 minutes. Don't remove the cover during this time.
Fluff the rice with a damp wooden paddle.
Drape a kitchen towel over the pot and cover with the pot lid until serving.
Makes 6 cups.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; cool.
Add cooked shrimp and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 cup oleo.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish and alternate carrots, onions, cheese and soup until used.
Melt 4 tablespoons of oleo in flat pan.
Stir in seasoned cubes and spread over top just before baking.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hodge podge soup
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain.
Add undiluted beans, tomatoes and soup.
Cook over medium heat for about 30 minutes.

title: million dollar candy
directions: Stir
Eagle
Brand
milk
and
melted butter; pour over sugar, coconut,
pecans
and
vanilla.
Mix well and roll into balls. Melt
chocolate chips and paraffin together. Dip balls into this mixture, then place on a foil sheet and let harden.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and 1 cup applesauce; add the other cup with soda mixed well.
Add flour in small amounts, mixing well.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Wash lima beans.
Soak overnight in an 8-quart pot.
Mostly full of water.
Cook in the same water for about 1 1/2 hours until the skin cracks when blown.
(Caution:
Water foams over very easily.)
Drain and add bacon, sugar, catsup and mustard.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until tender.

title: "after a long day lasagne"
directions: Cook noodles; put layer in baking dish.
Brown ground beef; mix into Ragu.
Put layer of meat sauce on noodles, then layer of cottage cheese, then layer of Mozzarella.
Repeat each layer. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chilled peach soup
directions: Combine peaches into blender with 1 cup milk and ice cubes. Process on medium speed until pureed.
Add remaining 1/2 cup milk, sour cream, honey, ginger and nutmeg.
Blend well.
Garnish with sliced strawberry and sliced kiwi.
Serves 4.
Contains 181 calories and 1.2 grams fat.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix eggs with tuna.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes in oven.
May top with potato chips.
Oven temperature: 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cheese, Jell-O and drained pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown beef and onion together, crumbling meat with a fork.
Spread in casserole dish.
Spread cooked macaroni over meat.
Pour pizza sauce over macaroni and toss lightly.
Top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: dad's dish
directions: In a large skillet, brown the ground beef and onion.
Drain any fluid off the beef.
Add the green chiles, drain the corn and add to the skillet.
Add the beans, salt and pepper.
Heat until hot, then serve with picante sauce and tortillas.
Sprinkle with shredded Monterey Jack cheese.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, water and salt in a large Dutch oven.
Simmer covered about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mash mixture once or twice with a potato masher, leaving some vegetable pieces whole.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until soup is thoroughly heated.
Yield:
7 cups.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Blend in dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Heat for 45 minutes.

title: chicken noodle cheese bake
directions: Mix together and sprinkle some of both cheeses on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy rice medley
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Continue cooking until butter is melted and vegetables are heated through.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: If using fresh sweet potatoes, place in a pan.
Cover with water and cook, covered, for 25 to 35 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Cool slightly.
Peel and cut into chunks.
Place cooked or canned yams in 2-quart baking dish.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, syrup, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: cheesy ham grill
directions: Top 1 slice of bread with processed cheese, ham, marmalade, mustard and second bread slice.
Spread sandwich with margarine. Cook in skillet on medium heat until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: oreo ice cream cake dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and reserve a cup of crumbs for top of cake and put the rest of the crumbs in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer the vanilla ice cream or ice milk (softened). Next, pour the caramel topping and the chocolate topping followed by the roasted peanuts. Then smooth on the container of Cool Whip. Put it in the freezer.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box.
Cool layers overnight or until real cool.
Mix sour cream with coconut and sugar.
Split layers; fill with mixture.
Save out 1 cup of what is left and mix with Cool Whip.
Ice cake with mixture.
Put in airtight container and freeze 2 days.

title: oven-barbecued chicken
directions: Sauce:
In a medium saucepan, combine tomato sauce, orange sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until thickened.
Place chicken in baking pan. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Brush sauce over chicken and bake 20 minutes more.
Brush with sauce during the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: cheese almond toasts
directions: Mix
cheese,
mayonnaise
and
seasonings.
Add
onion, almonds and bacon.	Spread on slices of crustless bread, which has been cut into quarters.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter; add broth and bring to boil.
Add the broccoli; cook until it is tender.
Add milk, noodles, cheese, salt and garlic powder.
Simmer for about one hour.

title: braised sirloin tips over rice
directions: Brown meat on all sides in shortening or oil in large skillet. Stir in consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: sherried walnuts
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spread on cookie sheets to dry.

title: sausage and egg breakfast casserole
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Spray 9 x 13 baking dish with cooking spray.
Butter one side of bread and place in baking dish to cover the bottom.
Spread sausage over bread.
Mix together 6 eggs and 2 cups of milk and pour over sausage and bread.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
For seasoning, may use salt or garlic salt and pepper on top.
Place in refrigerator overnight covered with aluminum foil or may be baked and served immediately.

title: cheesy bacon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Paper line 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, oats and bacon bits.
Combine egg, milk, oil and cheese.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cup 2/3 full and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour with	lid on. If too thick, add water.

title: reece's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients by hand in mixing bowl.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add margarine to mixture and mix well.
Press in two oblong pans (ungreased) 7 x 11 inch.
Melt Hershey milk chocolate in 250° oven for 15 minutes.
Melt 1/2 block paraffin over hot water.
Stir in chocolate.
Mix well.
Pour over other ingredients in pans.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Pour on hot griddle.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in heavy saucepan. Heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling point.

title: shereens' eggplant curry
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash and dry eggplants.
Slash gashes in eggplants and bake for 1 hour in oven.
Discard the skin and smash pulp in a bowl.
Combine eggplant, tomatoes, coriander, cumin, turmeric and red pepper in a bowl and stir until blended. In a skillet, heat the Crisco until hot.
Add the garlic and stir for 15 seconds; drop in the ginger and stir for 15 seconds.
Add the onions and stir until soft.
Add eggplant and stir until most of the liquid is gone and mixture is thick and pulls away from the side of the pan.
Add garam masala.
Serve on a heated platter or transfer to a heated bowl.
Top with fresh coriander and lemon juice.

title: momma loebbaka's spaghetti
directions: Brown beef with onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Drain grease.
Brown with tomato paste and spices.
Add other cans; bring to a boil, cover and cut back to a simmer.
Cook up to 4 hours or as long as desired.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Place spinach in bowl; wring out all water until dry.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet on medium heat.
Add onion and mushrooms; saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Place sour cream, bread crumbs and eggs in bowl. Attach bowl and flat beater.
On speed 4, beat 30 seconds.
Add spinach, onion, mushrooms, Cheddar cheese, Swiss cheese, basil and oregano.
On speed 2, mix 30 seconds, until combined.

title: pineapple-walnut cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let dough thaw several hours.
Spread on greased cookie sheet out to edges.
Separate egg.
Brush dough with yolk.
Place pepperoni in rows to cover dough.
Place Provolone on top evenly. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and oregano.

title: cranberry butter
directions: In a food processor with metal blade inserted, or in a blender, coarsely chop cranberries with powdered sugar and lemon peel.
Add butter and blend until mixture is combined, but slightly chunky.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bring to room temperature before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening, stirring until shortening is melted.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Blend well (batter will be stiff).
Fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool for 30 minutes before pouring on icing.

title: orange date nut cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk to the first 3 ingredients.
Add the dates, orange rind and nuts; mix.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 350° for an hour and 15 minutes, or until firm.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, Karo syrup and margarine for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
While waiting, spray brown paper bag with Pam and put corn in.
When mixture is done cooking, take out of microwave and add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir until foamy.
Pour over corn. Close bag and shake to coat.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out and shake.
Return to microwave.
Cook 30 seconds.
Again, take out and shake.
Cook 30 seconds more.
Shake.
Pour out on waxed paper and let cool.

title: pomanders
directions: Stud fruit with whole cloves, leaving enough space between some rows for ribbon for hanging.
After all cloves are in, combine spices and roll pomander in spices.
Keep pomanders in the spice filled bowl in a warm dry place.
Lasts 1 week.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: linguini and hot clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic, jalapeno and onions (cut in small pieces) in olive oil and juice from clams until tender.
Continue to add juice until sauce turns milkier than what it is in the bottle; add the clams and parsley; continue to heat with additional juice for 15 to 20 minutes.
You can add white dry wine for different taste when sauteing.

title: fried mush
directions: Put in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water for about an hour.
Stir about 4 times.
Pour in loaf dish and cool overnight in refrigerator.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Roll in flour and sprinkle with sugar.
Brown in butter or Crisco in skillet until crispy on each side.

title: poppy seed prepared rolls
directions: Slice bread in half; fill with cheese and ham.
Melt butter; add poppy seed, minced onion, sugar and Durkee sauce.
Pour over rolls.
Cook in oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes (will look a little burnt, but aren't).
Each roll can be cut in half and served as finger sandwiches.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Precook rice and chop broccoli before cooking.
Add all ingredients together.
Bake in 350° oven until onion and celery are done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: rachel's marble coffee cake
directions: Beat together the butter, sugar, eggs and sour cream; add the flour, baking powder and baking soda and beat well.
Put half the batter in a greased (with cooking spray) tube pan.
Mix the remaining batter with the cocoa, then put in tube pan on top of white batter; swirl the 2 batters together.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: virginia's baked custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt and continue beating until well blended, then add hot milk slowly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a baking dish which has been rinsed in cold water.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set baking dish in pan of hot water and bake (350°) until custard is set or a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add soups, sauce and peppers. Bring to a boil.
In casserole dish, layer chips, sauce and cheese.
Repeat with cheese being on top when finished.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Fast dish.

title: spiced candy apple rings
directions: Cut apples into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in vinegar water to prevent browning.
Tie cloves, allspice and nutmeg in a spice bag. Combine sugar, water, vinegar and red hots, spice bag and lemon. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir until candy is dissolved.
Drain apples and add to syrup.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; beat.
Drop on wax paper with a teaspoon.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients with hands until thoroughly mixed.
Form small balls and place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chopped chicken, eggs and vegetables in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken broth and soups together.
Pour mixture over other ingredients.
Mix flour, milk and mayonnaise, then spoon over soup mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until golden brown.

title: sausage-egg brunch bake
directions: Trim, butter and cube bread and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and salt in blender.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: amber's corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: baked garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove the papery outer skins from the garlic, leaving the cloves intact.
Arrange the heads in a baking dish just large enough to hold them.
Add oil and chicken stock to dish and set in the middle of the oven.
Bake 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes or so until golden brown.
Serve immediately. Squeeze on French bread or Melba toast.
Serves 4.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In a glass jar or crock, alternate layers of cucumbers and onions.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.

title: caesar salad
directions: In very large salad bowl, mix with wire whisk:
juice from 1 lemon, 2 teaspoons anchovy paste, olive oil, fresh ground pepper and 3 large cloves garlic (minced).
Towel dry the romaine leaves and hand tear large pieces into bowl.
Toss very well just before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion in oil; add ground beef and brown it.
Add ingredients up to Parmesan cheese.
Add 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Simmer 30 minutes, covered.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Layer:
Meat sauce on bottom, layer of noodles, layer of Mozzarella cheese and layer of Parmesan cheese.
Repeat the layers ending with meat sauce.
Then add 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jewish cookie
directions: Spread over large pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Cut as desired before cold.

title: cran-grape cooler
directions: In a blender, place juices, strawberries and ice.
Process on medium speed until ice cubes are crushed.

title: baked corn chops
directions: Brown chops and put into a baking pan.
Combine bread, corn, onion and margarine; spread over chops.
Add water.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Combine sugar, coconut and sour cream; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Make cake mix according to directions.
Cool and split to make 4 layers.
Reserve 1 cup coconut mixture.
Spread remainder between layers.
Mix the Cool Whip with 1 cup of coconut mixture.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Pat with another package of frozen coconut, if desired.
Refrigerate.
This cake freezes well.

title: chicken casserole - the best
directions: Combine ingredients and place in ovenware dish.
Make topping with one stack Ritz crackers, crumbled in 1 stick melted margarine.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake until bubbly hot or about 30 minutes.
Serves about 8.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer cauliflower, lettuce and bacon.
Put some onion on each layer.
Put Hellmann's mayonnaise on top and sprinkle with sugar and cheese.
Let set overnight.
Stir together before serving.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Remove any shells from crab meat.
Place in a large bowl. Add cracker crumbs and mix thoroughly with hands.

title: pear and pineapple preserves
directions: Mix together fruit and sugar.
Do not drain pineapple.
Bring slowly to boil and cook slow until fruit is done and jelled, stirring often.
Add the Jell-O and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Spoon hot preserves into sterile jars and seal.
Real good.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Sift
all dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients
and
mix
well.
Place
in 2 lightly greased bread pans and bake for approximately 1 hour at 325°.

title: spinach suprize
directions: Cook spinach; drain, keeping 1 cup of liquid.
Set spinach aside.
Melt butter; add onion and saute.
Add flour, milk and 1 cup liquid from spinach.
Cut cheese into cubes and add last 3 ingredients and spinach.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: hot salsa
directions: Ingredients needed will depend on how much you wish to make and how spicy you like it.
Combine all the ingredients in a blender and pulse to mix.
Do not overblend or it will turn to a thin liquid.
Blend only long enough to slightly chop and blend spices.
This will keep for 2 to 3 days in the refrigerator.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together in a storage container. This makes
servings
or
you can make per cup by using 2 rounded teaspoons per cup of hot water.
Better when let steep for a while.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into flowerets.
Chop green onions.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and seasoning.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
This salad is best if made ahead and put in an airtight container and tossed occasionally to coat vegetables.

title: summer coolness
directions: Cream together flour and stick of butter.
Add pecans and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° (don't brown). Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and spread on first mixture.
Mix boxes of pudding with milk and pour over cream cheese.
Add remaining Cool Whip on top.
Grate a chocolate candy bar over top, if desired.

title: fruit fingers
directions: Add sugar gradually to eggs, beating well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients, mincemeat and nuts.
Pour into a pan about 9 x 14-inches, greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake in a slow oven, 300°, for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm into narrow strips and roll in powdered sugar.
Yields 36 bars.

title: church stew
directions: Place stew meat on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer the carrots, then onions and last the potatoes on top.
Mix together the soups and the ginger ale.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 to 3
hours.

title: county kitchen casserole
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet until browned; drain, crumble and set aside.
Spread croutons on bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
Cover croutons with Cheddar and Pepper Jack cheeses.
Sprinkle cooked sausage and onion over cheeses.

title: handprint cutouts(eatable)
directions: Mix together well:
shortening, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
If dough seems too stiff, add a little milk.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness.

title: spaghetti primavera with cheese sauce
directions: Prepare pasta as directed.
Cook garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Discard garlic.
Add broccoli and red pepper; stir constantly until coated with oil.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Cover and cook on medium until broccoli is tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Reduce to low; add Cheez Whiz, milk, Parmesan and oregano, stirring constantly until cheese dissolves and mixture is blended.
Drain pasta; place in serving bowl.
Pour cheese sauce over pasta, carefully tossing to mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush cookies; set aside 1 cup of the cookies.
Melt butter and mix in the crushed cookies.
Place in oblong pan.
Let set 1 hour.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Set aside and mix pudding as directions on box.

title: hamburger crunch
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet.
Drain.
Mix in rice, soup, milk, water, soy sauce and pepper.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, about 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is done.

title: flan caramel custard(spain)
directions: Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar in skillet until golden brown, stirring constantly.
While hot, spread evenly over bottom of shallow 2-quart casserole dish (cool).
In bowl, beat eggs until foamy; gradually add remaining cup of sugar.
Beat well after each addition.
Scald milk with cinnamon stick.
Gradually add hot milk to egg mixture, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour into casserole.
Place casserole in hot water and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: wisconsin cream cheese mints
directions: Beat cheese by mixer or hand until soft; add color and flavor. Knead until pie dough consistency (a firmer candy is made by decreasing sugar).

title: hearty casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onion and cook until transparent. Then add meat and continue to cook until meat loses its reddish color.
Set aside to cool.
Mix the cheese, drained macaroni, mustard, corn, salt, pepper and tomato soup.
Stir in the mixture of meat and onion.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve piping hot.

title: cheesy italian broccoli bake
directions: Cook noodles; drain and stir in oil.
Cook broccoli; drain. Combine cottage cheese and sour cream.
Layer 1/3 noodles, 1/2 broccoli, 1/3 spaghetti sauce and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese in lightly greased cake pan.
Repeat layers once.
Spoon cottage cheese over Mozzarella cheese.
Top with 1/3 noodles and sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine chili sauce, water and grape jelly.
Heat and stir to melt jelly.
Pour over cabbage rolls and bake 45 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 28 to 30 rolls.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and creamed mix.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; mix again.
Add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Mix.
Drop by one teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 or 9 minutes.
Makes 100 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownie mix as directed.
Crumble or break up Heath bars; set aside.
In a glass trifle dish or glass salad bowl, layer ingredients as follows:
1/2 brownies, 1/2 chocolate mousse, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 Heath bars.
Repeat.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: In large bowl, cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in mashed bananas, drained pineapple and nuts. Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into banana mixture until smooth. Spoon into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Wrap airtight in foil or plastic wrap.
Let stand overnight for easy slicing and spread with cream cheese, if desired.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Drain well the pineapple chunks, peaches and cranberries. Layer fruit, ending with cranberries.
Dust with brown sugar.
Dab with sweet butter.
Pour dry sherry over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: egg salad
directions: Boil and mash egg.
Stir in mayonnaise, prepared mustard, chopped olives, finely chopped dill pickle and bacon fried crisp and drained.

title: cheese twists
directions: On lightly floured pastry sheet, unfold 1 of the pie crusts. Roll out with rolling pin until crust is 12-inch square.
Brush with 1 tablespoon of melted margarine and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
Fold each strip in half lengthwise, pinch together and twist.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain off grease.
Slice cheese into thin slices.
Put in the meat.
Stir in until it melts.
Add bottle of taco sauce.
Add chopped up onion.
Add garlic (chopped up).
Turn heat on.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Add water to raisins and boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in soda. Let stand.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla, beaten eggs and raisins with their liquid.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop by small spoonfuls on a greased baking sheet, leaving plenty of space between.
Bake at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil butter, sugar, cocoa, milk and vanilla for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Blend together shortening, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and butter in a heavy saucepan. Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring to 300° or when syrup separates into hard brittle threads when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla, baking soda and peanuts.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
When slightly cooled, pull edges to make a thin sheet.
When thoroughly cold, break into pieces.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds candy.

title: holiday cranberry mold
directions: Carefully wash cranberries; discard stems and any soft berries.
In a 2-quart saucepan, heat 1 cup juice, the cranberries and sugar to boiling over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer until berries pop, about 5 minutes.
Refrigerate 6-cup mold.
In small bowl, sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup juice.
Let stand 5 minutes to soften. Add to hot cranberry mixture along with salt; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour mixture into 2-quart bowl.
Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches consistency of unbeaten egg white, about 1 hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Mix all together and put into casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yummy hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper; add corn, tomatoes and sauce.
Mix well.
Mix cornbread; pour it over the top of meat mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until cornbread is done.

title: moo's apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Make dough. Roll into a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples, then sprinkle apples evenly over dough. Roll up dough like cinnamon roll. Dampen edges with water and seal. Slice dough into about 16 slices 1/2-inch thick.
Place in pan with melted butter. Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings. Always use 2 cups liquid.

title: peanutty banana squares
directions: Fold sugar and liqueur into whipped cream.
Refrigerate.
Blend peanut butter and hot fudge.
Working quickly, spread fresh banana ice cream evenly in an 8-inch square pan.
With knife, mark off squares, 3 across and 3 down.
With back of spoon, make an indentation in center of each square.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of peanut butter fudge mixture into each indentation.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup crushed peanut butter around indents.
Spread chocolate chip ice cream over all.
Gently press down to level top.
Swirl whipping cream mixture over top.
Sprinkle with remaining crushed peanut butter.
Peanut butter fudge filling will be centered in each square.
Freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
To serve, cut into 9 squares.

title: yummy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients, including raisins.
Add slowly to sugar mixture until blended.
Put heaping spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: looney's cookies
directions: Mix
bowl 1 ingredients together by hand until creamy.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Put half bacon in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer rest of ingredients, ending with rest of bacon.
Pour catsup over all. Bake (uncovered) at 350° for 3 hours.

title: corn stuffed tomato cups
directions: Scoop out centers of tomatoes. Heat butter in skillet. Add corn, onion, pepper, salt and bread crumbs, then stir mixture. Cook together 5 minutes. Use the mixture to stuff the tomatoes. Put in greased pan and cook in 400° oven for 40 minutes or until tender. Baste about 3 times with butter to which a little water has been added. Serve with steak or hamburgers or Mexican food.
